    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89699979849?pwd=gCwoAEcIgnve6d5ofbkJaMVX2NsPYI.1',
    '{"id":"01K8Y5Z3H8VP7G6DH216RN9PQR","title":"Tristan Pelligrino and Barb Willans","summary":{"notes":"## **Salesforce-Marketo Integration and Lead Scoring**\n\nThe meeting clarified key aspects of the Salesforce-Marketo integration and lead scoring systems to ensure accurate data flow and lead qualification.\n\n- **The Salesforce-Marketo sync runs every five minutes**, moving new and updated data bidirectionally between the systems, as confirmed by Justin (04:23).  \n    - The integration uses the Marketo user for authentication, driving all sync activity.  \n    - Lead and contact objects sync is configured through field mapping within Marketo’s database management, distinguishing standard and custom fields.  \n    - Justin highlighted that certain custom objects sync differently and the default lead/contact sync settings remain mostly unchanged over time.  \n    - This frequent sync supports near real-time lead updates and accurate sales follow-up readiness.\n\n- **Lead scoring is driven by smart campaigns focused primarily on webinars and other activities** (05:36).  \n    - Product Showcase webinars assign **100 points** immediately, flagging attendees for follow-up, while Thought Leadership webinars score lower to reflect top-of-funnel engagement.  \n    - Scoring templates are managed centrally and copied for each webinar program, enabling consistent scoring practices.  \n    - The scoring model combines **engagement score** (actions like email clicks, webinar attendance) and **demographic score** (profile fit), which together create the total **lead score** that determines qualification.  \n    - Justin noted some legacy scoring fields exist but the person score in Marketo maps to the lead score in Salesforce, which currently drives lead qualification.\n\n## **Lead Lifecycle and Qualification Process**\n\nThe team reviewed the lead-to-contact conversion process and how Marketing Qualified Leads (MQLs) are created, managed, and reported.\n\n- **New leads created in Marketo flow into Salesforce as lead records and require manual conversion to contacts by BDRs** (08:44).  \n    - When a lead hits the **100-point MQL threshold**, a task is created for the BDR to qualify and convert the lead to a contact and account, creating an opportunity in the process.  \n    - Existing contacts generate new opportunities without conversion steps.  \n    - The BDR’s workflow centers on a task-based model rather than direct lead record updates, with qualification notes and statuses tracked in tasks (36:30).  \n    - Maria emphasized that lead and contact stages are not actively used in current processes, focusing instead on task completion and opportunity progression (14:25).\n\n- **MQL reporting is primarily based on task activity reports, capturing lead qualification events** (15:17).  \n    - Justin demonstrated a report filtering activities with subjects containing “Marketing Qualified Lead” since mid-September, showing qualification types like hand raise, bubble up, or trade show (18:35).  \n    - Barb noted discrepancies between reported MQL counts and actual qualified leads, highlighting that some reported leads are already opportunities or support requests, which inflates the numbers (51:15).  \n    - This gap underscores the need to refine MQL definitions and reporting logic to improve accuracy and alignment with sales (51:24).\n\n## **Data Source of Truth and Migration Considerations**\n\nThe discussion outlined strategic decisions about data sources and synchronization rules for upcoming HubSpot migration.\n\n- **Salesforce is preferred as the primary source of truth for contact and lead data**, supported unanimously by Maria, Justin, and Barb (26:38).  \n    - Salesforce contains comprehensive records, including those absent from Marketo due to scoring or activity thresholds.  \n    - Marketo holds some records not in Salesforce, but these tend to lack critical data such as email or company info, limiting their sales value (26:41).  \n    - Effective deduplication and bidirectional sync between Salesforce and HubSpot are critical to maintain data integrity during migration.  \n    - Maria stressed syncing deletions from Salesforce to HubSpot to avoid stale or dead contacts lingering in sales systems, while deletions in HubSpot should not remove contacts from Salesforce to preserve records (30:34).\n\n- **Business rules around contact deletion focus on removing bad or invalid data rather than non-responsive leads** (29:11).  \n    - Maria and Kyle cautioned against deleting contacts solely due to lack of engagement to avoid losing sales relationships.  \n    - The team discussed using automation and enrichment tools to clean dormant contacts quarterly or annually, minimizing manual cleanup burden (32:13).\n\n## **Lead Qualification Workflow and Reporting**\n\nThe meeting detailed the BDR qualification workflow and reporting fields critical to sales and marketing alignment.\n\n- **BDRs work primarily through Salesforce tasks linked to leads, updating contact attempts and qualification notes without changing lead stages directly** (35:53).  \n    - Blake, the sole BDR currently, tracks up to three contact attempts and adds free-form qualification notes that feed into opportunity records (36:30).  \n    - The qualification notes field drives multiple reports and includes keywords like “Direct Flip” to flag known opportunities needing no further qualification (42:50).  \n    - Maria and Kyle highlighted that automating “Direct Flip” handling would save BDR time and reduce manual effort (43:38).\n\n- **Opportunity stages and field history tracking support handoffs from BDRs to sales reps**, distinguishing between marketing-qualified prospects and sales-qualified leads (44:32).  \n    - Opportunities typically enter as “Generate Prospect” and move to “Qualified” once sales confirms interest, forming the basis for sales pipeline reporting.  \n    - The team acknowledged that “Generate Prospect” represents a limbo stage where marketing has qualified but sales has not yet accepted the lead (46:12).  \n    - Reports rely heavily on tracking these stage changes and qualification notes to measure pipeline health and BDR effectiveness.\n\n- **Current reporting relies on filtering task subjects and free-text qualification notes**, a process the team wants to replace with more structured fields in HubSpot for better accuracy and easier management (53:11).  \n    - Maria emphasized recreating the task-based concept in HubSpot but without custom tasks, aiming for cleaner data and improved reporting workflows (53:37).\n\n## **Product and System Strategy for HubSpot Migration**\n\nThe conversation concluded with strategic considerations for lead/contact management in HubSpot and system simplification.\n\n- **Preference exists for using contact records over leads in HubSpot to simplify sales workflows and reporting** (55:57).  \n    - Maria prefers contacts only, citing easier sales rep adoption and fewer duplicate or messy lead records.  \n    - Tristan noted HubSpot introduced a lead object only recently, with many customers choosing to avoid leads entirely to reduce complexity (56:20).  \n    - The HubSpot model can link contacts directly to accounts, reducing the need for manual lead conversion steps seen in Salesforce-Marketo flows (55:50).\n\n- **The migration offers an opportunity to redesign the foundation of lead and contact management**, shedding legacy complexity and building streamlined processes (55:50).  \n    - Justin and Tristan see this as a chance to peel back layers and enable a cleaner, more effective CRM and marketing automation setup.  \n    - This includes defining clear business rules, data flows, and success metrics aligned with both sales and marketing needs.  \n    - The team aims to improve reporting accuracy, reduce manual work for BDRs, and ensure data cleanliness post-migration.\n\n- **Ongoing collaboration between marketing, sales, and technical teams is critical** to finalize data definitions, reporting standards, and workflows before migration (53:11).  \n    - Barb, Maria, and Kyle will help clarify MQL definitions and reporting needs to guide system design.  \n    - Tristan and Kyle will leverage experience from similar HubSpot migrations to anticipate challenges and solutions.  \n    - The plan involves phased implementation with test contacts and iterative validation to ensure smooth transition.","outline":null,"keywords":["Marketo Salesforce integration","Lead scoring model","Marketing qualified leads (MQL)","Salesforce task management","Data migration HubSpot","Lead/contact lifecycle"],"overview":"- **Salesforce-Marketo Sync:** Runs every five minutes, ensuring real-time data flow and accurate lead updates.  \n- **Lead Scoring Method:** Webinars score leads using engagement and demographic metrics; 100 points for Product Showcase.  \n- **MQL Creation Process:** Leads become contacts when reaching 100 points; BDRs are tasked with conversion and opportunity creation.  \n- **Source of Truth:** Salesforce is preferred for accurate lead data; critical to manage deduplication during HubSpot migration.  \n- **Contact Strategy for HubSpot:** Focus on contacts over leads to simplify workflows; eliminates manual conversions and enhances reporting.  \n- **Collaborative Work:** Marketing and sales must agree on definitions and reporting to prepare for a successful migration process.","action_items":"\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nReview and document detailed lead scoring model tokens and workflow in Marketo for complete understanding (07:46)\nAnalyze Salesforce reporting on MQLs and opportunity creation to confirm data attributes for management reporting (15:17)\nAssess and plan testing strategy with creation of test contacts in Salesforce to understand data flow and field behavior without impacting live data (24:07)\nMap out lead and contact object use in HubSpot for migration, considering simplifying data model as per meeting discussion (55:00)\n\n**Maria**\nProvide further clarification on MQL definitions and usage within AQI marketing and sales processes (17:00)\nAssist with examples and review of Salesforce reporting and workflows, including qualification notes and task management (37:00)\nSupport decision making on synchronization rules between HubSpot and Salesforce for record deletion and data cleanliness (28:06)\n\n**Kyle Scoville**\nProvide links to test account and key Salesforce reports used by BDRs for replication/testing purposes (24:39)\nSupport review of daily/weekly marketing management dashboards and reports relevant to MQLs and sales qualification (47:26)\n\n**Barb Willans**\nShare key marketing daily management reports and clarify weekly vs daily meeting cadence (47:27)\nProvide insights on MQL reporting differences and challenges for improved accuracy moving forward (48:45)\n"},"duration":57.709999084472656,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"id":1,"name":"Maria"},{"id":2,"name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"id":3,"name":"Justin"},{"id":4,"name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"id":5,"name":"bwillans"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Justin, how''s it going?","index":0,"end_time":1.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":1,"end_time":2.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.08,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Right.","index":2,"end_time":5.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think looks like just Barb, I believe we''re waiting on.","index":3,"end_time":8.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":5.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And did.","index":4,"end_time":10.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":10.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Did Barb send you all the.","index":5,"end_time":12.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":10.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"An agenda beforehand?","index":6,"end_time":14.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":12.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Not sure if she sent that or not, but yeah.","index":7,"end_time":18.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":8,"end_time":19.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":19.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Oh, it looks like here.","index":9,"end_time":21.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":20.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Here''s Barb now, but for today.","index":10,"end_time":25.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":21.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And we got Maria coming in here as well.","index":11,"end_time":29.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Hey, Barb.","index":12,"end_time":33.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":32.36,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Hey, guys.","index":13,"end_time":34.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.8,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So, all right, so we have a party here Friday afternoon.","index":14,"end_time":38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":35.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":15,"end_time":38.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":38,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":16,"end_time":39.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":39.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I don''t know if we need everyone for the whole hour, but my thought was in talking with Barb and sending the.","index":17,"end_time":46.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":39.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The agenda, you know, we''ve had an opportunity to get into Marketo Salesforce instances, navigate around, take a look at sample real data, take a look at recent records that have been created and a lot of what we want to just talk through today.","index":18,"end_time":63.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":46.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I actually want to pull up both Marketo and Salesforce just to have you all guide me into some of the right spots just so I know exactly where configuration is in place to also confirm field names and which ones are more important and how certain data gets to in certain places.","index":19,"end_time":84.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":63.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s what I had planned.","index":20,"end_time":86.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":84.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We could probably just utilize your time for the first 30 minutes and then I''ll.","index":21,"end_time":92.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":86.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''ll stick on with Barb to.","index":22,"end_time":93.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":92.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"To go through some of the things that we''re thinking about.","index":23,"end_time":96.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":94.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So how''s that sound for.","index":24,"end_time":97.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":96.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"For everyone?","index":25,"end_time":97.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":97.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, good.","index":26,"end_time":101.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let me share my screen.","index":27,"end_time":103.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":101.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I wanted to just start with probably on the Marketo side.","index":28,"end_time":107.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":103.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I had some questions on where the.","index":29,"end_time":109.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":107.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Configuration is share here.","index":30,"end_time":112.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":109.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I''m thinking this is probably Justin for you.","index":31,"end_time":118.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":113.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":32,"end_time":118.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":118.01,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''m guessing.","index":33,"end_time":119.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":118.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I want to make sure I''m in the right spot.","index":34,"end_time":122.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":120.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So Salesforce Marketo can be done through the.","index":35,"end_time":125.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":122.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The Marketo app.","index":36,"end_time":125.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":125.01,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then I also see here we have the Salesforce integration and the object sync.","index":37,"end_time":129.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":125.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"My question is, and I want to make sure I''m in the right spot.","index":38,"end_time":135.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":130.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"These objects, the lead in contacts, the sync is actually turned off.","index":39,"end_time":140.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":136.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I want to make sure I''m in the right spot because I see the Salesforce.","index":40,"end_time":145.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":141.06,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You want to click on the other Salesforce one.","index":41,"end_time":147.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":145.38,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":42,"end_time":147.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":147.14,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":43,"end_time":148.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":147.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":44,"end_time":148.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":148.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So tell me exactly like how the fields are mapped and kind of what''s driving the integration right now.","index":45,"end_time":156.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":150.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, there should be.","index":46,"end_time":157.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":156.5,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And maybe under Edit sync options, there''s a spot where you can choose.","index":47,"end_time":162.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":159.22,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"No.","index":48,"end_time":165.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":164.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean once we set these up, we typically just leave it forever the same way.","index":49,"end_time":172.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":168.59,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"But there''s usually maybe go back to the Salesforce object sync.","index":50,"end_time":175.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":172.35,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"No, you know where it is is under field management, under database management.","index":51,"end_time":183.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":179.07,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":52,"end_time":184.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":183.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":53,"end_time":184.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":184.47,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Let me go back there.","index":54,"end_time":185.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":184.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think have that screen open up already.","index":55,"end_time":187.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":56,"end_time":188.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No, I was just on that shape on that screen.","index":57,"end_time":190.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":188.35,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Yep.","index":58,"end_time":191.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":191.47,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"And then.","index":59,"end_time":192.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":191.91,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Oh, there.","index":60,"end_time":192.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":192.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then field mapping is where you want to find it.","index":61,"end_time":197.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":194.6,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"So the one that you''re on was the Salesforce object sync.","index":62,"end_time":201.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":198.84,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"That''s just for custom objects or adding some special stuff.","index":63,"end_time":204.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":201.32,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"It''s not going to be the default lead contact, opportunity objects.","index":64,"end_time":209.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":204.2,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Got it.","index":65,"end_time":210.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":210.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":66,"end_time":211.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":211.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So, all right, here we go.","index":67,"end_time":214,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Anything here, if you like, pop open one of them, it''ll show you the name of the object in Salesforce and what that field API name is in Salesforce.","index":68,"end_time":223.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":214,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"So, all right, it''s account type on contact and account type on lead.","index":69,"end_time":228.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":223.66,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And then underscore.","index":70,"end_time":228.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":228.14,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Underscore C just means it''s a custom field.","index":71,"end_time":231.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":228.94,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"It''s not an out of the box Salesforce field.","index":72,"end_time":233.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":231.02,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Got.","index":73,"end_time":233.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, this is perfect.","index":74,"end_time":234.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":233.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, so this helps me.","index":75,"end_time":235.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":234.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then the user.","index":76,"end_time":237.419,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":236.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we''re using the Marketo user, which is the one that''s authenticated here.","index":77,"end_time":240.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":237.419,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Looks like that''s the one that''s driving all of the.","index":78,"end_time":243.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":240.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"On the other side.","index":79,"end_time":245.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":244.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":80,"end_time":246.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so that helps me there.","index":81,"end_time":247.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":246.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That was one of my biggest questions.","index":82,"end_time":250.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":248.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The.","index":83,"end_time":251.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":251.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The next thing is, I believe Justin, you had mentioned this sync occurs like, like every five minutes or so.","index":84,"end_time":261.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":251.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is that right?","index":85,"end_time":262.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":86,"end_time":263.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":263.35,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"So every five minutes they''ll check to see if there''s anything new in Marketo and it''ll send that to Salesforce.","index":87,"end_time":268.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":263.75,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Anything new in Salesforce it''ll send back to Marketo.","index":88,"end_time":270.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":268.15,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"But you can also force a sync in between those times too.","index":89,"end_time":274.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":271.27,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Or certain actions you take might initiate a sync.","index":90,"end_time":279.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":275.38,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"It''s just that there''s any data outside of those things that change.","index":91,"end_time":283.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":280.1,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"It''s typically every five minutes.","index":92,"end_time":285.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":283.82,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"You can see those under.","index":93,"end_time":286.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":285.14,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"I think the, the sync status part, maybe it''ll show you how often it''s.","index":94,"end_time":291.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":286.58,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Which objects it''s sinking and how often it''s doing it.","index":95,"end_time":293.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":291.22,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Yeah, so product getting, you know, updates, deletes, new whatever, and kind of shows you how often it''s doing it and which objects it''s doing.","index":96,"end_time":305.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":293.78,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"All right, so that confirms that.","index":97,"end_time":307.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":305.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Now the next piece, Justin, while we have you, is on the lead scoring side.","index":98,"end_time":312.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":307.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I know there are a lot of like, smart campaigns that drive scores.","index":99,"end_time":317.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":313.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I wanted to know.","index":100,"end_time":319.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":317.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''m trying to follow the breadcrumbs, like which ones are.","index":101,"end_time":324.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":320.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Are the major drivers, at least from your perspective.","index":102,"end_time":327.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":324.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":103,"end_time":328.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I''ll go back through and kind.","index":104,"end_time":329.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":328.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Of put the pieces together.","index":105,"end_time":331.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":329.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":106,"end_time":331.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":331.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But I, I was just like interested on your side, like which ones to.","index":107,"end_time":334.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":331.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Really pay attention to.","index":108,"end_time":335.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I would say the webinar ones are the most problematic for AQI right now because there is two different types and sometimes there''s some confusion around that.","index":109,"end_time":346.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":336.69,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"So the TL ones where you see like aqi, wbnr, TL are Thought leadership ones.","index":110,"end_time":353.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":347.41,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"They''re supposed to be.","index":111,"end_time":354.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":353.25,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Yeah, a lower score because they are more top of the funnel.","index":112,"end_time":359.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":355.09,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And then ones that say PS instead are Product Showcase.","index":113,"end_time":362.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":359.41,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"They''re a demo of the AQI software.","index":114,"end_time":365.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":362.5,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"They''re supposed to be.","index":115,"end_time":365.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":365.02,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Anybody who attends it is to be followed up with, which means it would be 100 points immediately.","index":116,"end_time":372.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":365.98,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And then there was one that ran a couple weeks ago that we copied from a really old program from like 2023.","index":117,"end_time":378.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":372.74,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"We had vastly different scoring model in 2023, but the scoring, if you click on the.","index":118,"end_time":385.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":378.22,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"The program itself.","index":119,"end_time":386.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":385.87,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"So like the little calendar icon kind of deal.","index":120,"end_time":389.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":386.99,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Is this the best one here?","index":121,"end_time":391.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":389.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That one''s fine.","index":122,"end_time":392.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":391.87,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"You''ll see the score under my tokens.","index":123,"end_time":395.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":392.91,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"So all this, the score is set at the template level.","index":124,"end_time":397.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":395.23,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"When we copy this webinar template, where you see like my dot score dash attended says plus 60, that''s where you would set that.","index":125,"end_time":407.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":397.75,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"So at the template there''ll be like a folder that''s called like Webinar Templates that we''ve set it at that level and we just copy that template every time.","index":126,"end_time":416.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":407.55,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":127,"end_time":417.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":416.44,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"There is another part within here that is scoring for other activities that are not webinars.","index":128,"end_time":421.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":417.72,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"It''s a whole folder that just does scoring.","index":129,"end_time":423.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":421.68,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"But because webinars have a bunch of other stuff going on with them, we do the scoring at the program.","index":130,"end_time":429,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":423.72,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And which folder is that?","index":131,"end_time":430.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":429.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Just so I know, like the.","index":132,"end_time":431.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":430.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The base.","index":133,"end_time":432.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":431.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So here are the templates you''re talking about.","index":134,"end_time":433.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":432.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":135,"end_time":435.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":434.36,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Okay.","index":136,"end_time":435.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There should be something called like operational or Operational Flow.","index":137,"end_time":441.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":436.92,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"That did.","index":138,"end_time":441.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":441.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Remember seeing that.","index":139,"end_time":442.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":441.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"See, there we go.","index":140,"end_time":446.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I had that.","index":141,"end_time":447.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No, that''s just within that.","index":142,"end_time":448.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":447.12,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"It''s.","index":143,"end_time":448.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":448.32,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"It''s going to be a thankful.","index":144,"end_time":449.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":448.6,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Let me see if I can find it.","index":145,"end_time":451.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":449.6,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Operation Station.","index":146,"end_time":454.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Operation Station.","index":147,"end_time":456.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":455.36,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Yeah, Something weird, right?","index":148,"end_time":458.079,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":456.28,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And then one that is called Scoring Model.","index":149,"end_time":463.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":458.72,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"So we click on Scoring Model.","index":150,"end_time":464.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":463.4,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":151,"end_time":465.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":464.84,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Main one here.","index":152,"end_time":466.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If you click on the.","index":153,"end_time":467.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":466.56,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"The little suitcase folder itself, you''ll see all the tokens for the scoring model.","index":154,"end_time":471.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":467.48,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And again, here''s where you can tweak them all.","index":155,"end_time":474.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":472.69,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay, nice.","index":156,"end_time":475.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":474.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Equal means setting it to that number, plus means adding it, minus means and subtracting it.","index":157,"end_time":481.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":476.45,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":158,"end_time":482.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":481.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"100 points.","index":159,"end_time":483.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":483.17,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"You become a marketing qualified lead.","index":160,"end_time":485.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":483.81,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"All right.","index":161,"end_time":487.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":486.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so that''ll lead me to my next.","index":162,"end_time":489.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":487.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that helps me.","index":163,"end_time":490.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":489.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Two big things.","index":164,"end_time":491.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It was configuration, the field mapping make sure I was in the right spot and then the lead scoring.","index":165,"end_time":495.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":491.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this helps there.","index":166,"end_time":496.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":495.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I did want to pull up, like, for example, some just, like, recent data just to make sure I understand the flow.","index":167,"end_time":504.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":497.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It appears that.","index":168,"end_time":506.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":505.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So people records in Marketo are driving lead records in Salesforce.","index":169,"end_time":512.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":506.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":170,"end_time":512.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":512.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then I''m assuming folks convert it to contacts from there.","index":171,"end_time":518.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":514.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I just want to make sure, like.","index":172,"end_time":520.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":518.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know the normal life cycle that happens.","index":173,"end_time":523.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":520.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":174,"end_time":524.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":524.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So when a person hits 100 points in Marketo, it will create what''s called a marketing qualified lead task and attach that to either a leader contact in Salesforce that tells the lead qualifier or BDR or whatever terminology you want to use.","index":175,"end_time":541.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":524.9,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"I think Aki uses BDR to follow up with that person and to work the lead until they become an opportunity.","index":176,"end_time":549.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":541.7,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"At that point, they click a button on the task and convert the.","index":177,"end_time":554.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":549.9,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"If it''s a lead, it converts the lead to a contact and creates an account and creates an opportunity.","index":178,"end_time":561.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":556.89,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"If it was already a contact, it''ll just create a new opportunity.","index":179,"end_time":566.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":562.73,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":180,"end_time":567.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":567.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so for the.","index":181,"end_time":568.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":567.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So these are.","index":182,"end_time":569.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":568.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let me see.","index":183,"end_time":569.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":569.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Parameters I pulled.","index":184,"end_time":570.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.61,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":185,"end_time":571.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":570.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So these are not quite MQLs yet, because you''ll see their lead score is 99.","index":186,"end_time":574.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":571.13,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Right.","index":187,"end_time":574.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":574.29,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"So, yeah, so that''s a couple questions I have.","index":188,"end_time":577.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So these are folks I pulled.","index":189,"end_time":578.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":577.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Just anything create.","index":190,"end_time":580.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":579.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, Create date past September.","index":191,"end_time":582.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":580.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So these are all lead records.","index":192,"end_time":584.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":582.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it looks like the Marketo integrations creating these.","index":193,"end_time":590.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":586.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"They.","index":194,"end_time":591.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":591.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I could go back in the field mapping, which I wasn''t sure where, but this lead score is.","index":195,"end_time":597.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":592.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This is a formula field.","index":196,"end_time":599.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":597.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I wanted to know, like, how these differ and how those are driving right now.","index":197,"end_time":606.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":599.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know the field that''s mapped for lead score because there''s.","index":198,"end_time":610.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":606.97,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Unfortunately, AQ had a couple that they were using at different times.","index":199,"end_time":613.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":611.42,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Let me see the one that''s actually in use.","index":200,"end_time":619.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":617.98,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"I''m gonna make sure I tell you the right.","index":201,"end_time":644.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":643.03,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"The right field in Salesforce.","index":202,"end_time":662.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Tristan, you''re not looking for the tasks right now, right?","index":203,"end_time":670.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":667.04,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"You''re looking for the lead.","index":204,"end_time":671.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":670.08,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah, just looking at the.","index":205,"end_time":673.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":672.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The lead record that was created.","index":206,"end_time":676,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''ll be a good, good next step, though.","index":207,"end_time":678.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":676.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Maria, you''re on the.","index":208,"end_time":679.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, you might want to go to.","index":209,"end_time":683.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":680.8,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"On the upper left, there''s, like, nine dots.","index":210,"end_time":686.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":683.92,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"The BDR team uses the app called sales console.","index":211,"end_time":690.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":686.56,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Better view.","index":212,"end_time":692.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":692.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, it''ll pull up the task and the lead in one screen for them so that, like, you''re able to see them.","index":213,"end_time":701.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":693.5,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Tied.","index":214,"end_time":701.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":701.02,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"The field in Salesforce that maps to person score, and Marketo is called lead score.","index":215,"end_time":721.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":705.18,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"So that I don''t so it''s this.","index":216,"end_time":723.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":721.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"One, I think so I''m not sure what the calculator one is doing, but.","index":217,"end_time":728.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":723.55,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll take a look at that and just map.","index":218,"end_time":731.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":728.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it''s the, the person score in Marketo maps to lead score here.","index":219,"end_time":735.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":731.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":220,"end_time":737.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":737.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So engagement score too, which is.","index":221,"end_time":739.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":737.67,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Yeah, engagement is going to be actions they take and demographics call be who they are.","index":222,"end_time":745.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":741.15,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And then the lead score is a combination of engagement score and demographic score.","index":223,"end_time":751.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":745.87,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":224,"end_time":752.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":751.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, so that was this one demographic score that is.","index":225,"end_time":756.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":752.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And is that driven by like workflows as well in Marketo with a different scoring system?","index":226,"end_time":764.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":757.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":227,"end_time":764.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":764.35,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Yeah, demographic score just gives you like a bump up of like 10 or 20 points versus someone that doesn''t meet the ideal customer profile.","index":228,"end_time":773.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":767.56,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":229,"end_time":774.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":774.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I could probably.","index":230,"end_time":778.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":777,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Are they in stored in the same area, Justin, like as far as those, those flows or where''s the best place to find those?","index":231,"end_time":784.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":778.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, this is under demographics.","index":232,"end_time":786.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":785,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Oh, demographic scoring.","index":233,"end_time":787.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":786.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so this scoring model, I''ll research that so I can unlock the, the calculations there.","index":234,"end_time":793.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":787.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So demographics store, big piece there and then.","index":235,"end_time":796.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":794.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, saw eng.","index":236,"end_time":797.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":796.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This is just at a high level.","index":237,"end_time":800.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":798.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How''s that different from lead score?","index":238,"end_time":803.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":800.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Lead score is engagement score plus demographic score.","index":239,"end_time":807.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":804.34,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":240,"end_time":810.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":809.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, engagement is just what people do like click an email, attend a webinar.","index":241,"end_time":815.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":810.58,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":242,"end_time":816.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then fit score.","index":243,"end_time":818.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":817.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Fit score I think is something that Marketo just invents on their own.","index":244,"end_time":822.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":819.54,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"I''m not sure how they calculate that, but it''s nothing that I said.","index":245,"end_time":826.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":822.54,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":246,"end_time":827.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then we, we''re just pulling that.","index":247,"end_time":828.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":827.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Over so it, it ties to what''s over in Marketo.","index":248,"end_time":831.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, let see if I had anything else here.","index":249,"end_time":834.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":831.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so the other thing, so.","index":250,"end_time":841.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Lead type for all of these in lead stage is that I know recently all of these records, it''s, it''s always null.","index":251,"end_time":849.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":841.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But when do we set the actual lead stage?","index":252,"end_time":853.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":849.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That is not done until they are.","index":253,"end_time":856.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":854.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Converted to a contact.","index":254,"end_time":857.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":856.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is that right or how''s that process work?","index":255,"end_time":860.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":857.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Now.","index":256,"end_time":861.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":860.98,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"We don''t use lead stage or contact stage at all in our current processes unless like I believe there''s a marketing status that can be set to inactive and that might impact the stage of the lead.","index":257,"end_time":879.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":865.66,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"But it''s not something that like people manage or look at or really do anything with.","index":258,"end_time":885.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":880.26,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Okay.","index":259,"end_time":886.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":885.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this doesn''t drive any reporting or anything for you all.","index":260,"end_time":890.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":886.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":261,"end_time":890.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":890.34,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Used to be used, but when we switched to the task based model they stopped using.","index":262,"end_time":895.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":892.1,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":263,"end_time":898.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":896.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So if I want to pull.","index":264,"end_time":899.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":898.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This is my next question.","index":265,"end_time":901.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":900.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If I want to pull like the MQLS leads or contacts that have been converted to MQLs.","index":266,"end_time":908.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":901.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like what''s the best report or like data attribute to find.","index":267,"end_time":912.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":908.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like if I want to find the last 90 days.","index":268,"end_time":916.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":912.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This report called tasks and activities.","index":269,"end_time":920.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":917.95,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"This is.","index":270,"end_time":924.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":923.63,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Correct me if I''m wrong, but that''s what I usually have set up in talks.","index":271,"end_time":928.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":924.99,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And is that in.","index":272,"end_time":931.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":930.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Why is this.","index":273,"end_time":933.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Maria, you''re on mute.","index":274,"end_time":937.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":935.83,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"If you''re looking for converted.","index":275,"end_time":942.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":940.55,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"I''m sure the tasks and activities can probably get you there as well.","index":276,"end_time":946.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":943.35,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"But what we''ve been doing is looking opportunity creation with qualified source, I believe.","index":277,"end_time":954.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":946.43,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Right, Kai?","index":278,"end_time":955.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":954.87,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"It could be like created by Blake or Brittany or whoever.","index":279,"end_time":960.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":956.31,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":280,"end_time":960.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":960.49,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"And I can try and pull up.","index":281,"end_time":963.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":961.53,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Well, that''s going to be ones that have been converged in opportunity already, I think.","index":282,"end_time":966.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":963.69,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Tristan, are you looking for like people that are MQLs or people that are opportunities?","index":283,"end_time":973.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":966.49,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Yeah, I think the big, the big thing, you know, talking about, Barb, like a big metric on the marketing side is number of MQLs.","index":284,"end_time":980.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":973.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So like just trying to find.","index":285,"end_time":982.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":980.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I know there are a lot of definitions as to when that happens, but I.","index":286,"end_time":986.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":983.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because there are some date stored on the Salesforce record, like MQL date, but I don''t see that populated a lot.","index":287,"end_time":993.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":986.57,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So trying to figure out like what, you know, when you''re reporting the management or even when marketing''s working with sales, like how that, you know, the.","index":288,"end_time":1003.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":993.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The data attributes that we''re using to provide that number.","index":289,"end_time":1006.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1003.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Oh, so you''re saying basically like the number of inbound leads that are created.","index":290,"end_time":1011.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1007.33,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah, essentially that would be considered an mql.","index":291,"end_time":1018.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1012.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":292,"end_time":1020.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1019.45,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah, Justin is correct.","index":293,"end_time":1022.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1020.33,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"I think we might want to.","index":294,"end_time":1024.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1022.17,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Maybe I''m just out of the loop on what AQI defines as an mql because we have that generate prospect stage and opportunities and that''s often talked through as well.","index":295,"end_time":1037.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1026.25,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"But let''s.","index":296,"end_time":1038.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1037.93,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah, that might be something for later and maybe just like I''m out of the loop, maybe I need to catch up on it.","index":297,"end_time":1044.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1039.93,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"But yeah, it''s a good.","index":298,"end_time":1047.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1044.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Oh, sorry, what''s that, Barb?","index":299,"end_time":1048.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1047.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry.","index":300,"end_time":1049.88,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1049,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I think it''s a really good question about the definition around every single stage, but also looking at every stage to make sure that we''re.","index":301,"end_time":1057.52,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1050.52,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We are calculating not just an MQL but what happens prior.","index":302,"end_time":1061.88,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1057.52,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"What is a lead.","index":303,"end_time":1063.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1062.36,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I don''t think is an AQI part of the process right now.","index":304,"end_time":1069.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1064.28,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We go straight to mql.","index":305,"end_time":1071.88,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1070.04,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But.","index":306,"end_time":1072.52,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1072.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But actually it''s just getting a definition around each of these things is really important.","index":307,"end_time":1078.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1072.68,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And increasing the origin, like the input stage.","index":308,"end_time":1083.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1078.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":309,"end_time":1085.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1084.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And that''s a piece of it too, is like Making sure we have the definition right, you know, and we all agree on what that is.","index":310,"end_time":1092.549,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1085.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''ll be a piece of it as well.","index":311,"end_time":1093.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1092.549,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then making sure that the data reflects whatever that definition is.","index":312,"end_time":1097.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1093.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so let''s say.","index":313,"end_time":1101.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1099.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Oh, Maria went off screen.","index":314,"end_time":1103.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1101.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I was wondering.","index":315,"end_time":1103.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1103.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I was going to.","index":316,"end_time":1104.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1103.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Looks like this Graziti contact''s probably a.","index":317,"end_time":1107.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1104.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Test contact, but I was going to pull this up.","index":318,"end_time":1109.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1107.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I can share my screen and show you just if you want.","index":319,"end_time":1112.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1110.5,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Like I made a report in AQS Salesforce.","index":320,"end_time":1115.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1112.62,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":321,"end_time":1115.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1115.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If you don''t mind.","index":322,"end_time":1116.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1115.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That way you don''t see me fumbling around.","index":323,"end_time":1118.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1117.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''m not as used to things.","index":324,"end_time":1120.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1118.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''m doing my best here.","index":325,"end_time":1121.699,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1120.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let''s see.","index":326,"end_time":1122.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1121.699,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Wow.","index":327,"end_time":1123.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1122.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":328,"end_time":1123.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1123.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You should be good, Justin.","index":329,"end_time":1125.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1123.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this is.","index":330,"end_time":1131.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1130.5,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"I didn''t add all the information, but.","index":331,"end_time":1133.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1131.65,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Can you see my screen?","index":332,"end_time":1135.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1134.37,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Yes.","index":333,"end_time":1138.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1138.13,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"So I''m basically just using this activities as the leads report and pulling any activities where the subject is marketing qualified leads.","index":334,"end_time":1148.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1139.25,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And then we have different names for them depending on how they became a lead.","index":335,"end_time":1153.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1148.37,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"So hand raise is you fill out a form, bubble up means you reach 100 points.","index":336,"end_time":1157.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1153.25,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And trade show means you attended a trade show.","index":337,"end_time":1160.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1157.92,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"So I just did since September 16th.","index":338,"end_time":1162.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1160.44,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And then you should be able to click into the activity to see more information.","index":339,"end_time":1171.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1165.04,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"So in this case we want the activity.","index":340,"end_time":1176.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1174.08,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"You''ll see.","index":341,"end_time":1177.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1176.96,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Person put some notes in the comments as they''re qualifying them.","index":342,"end_time":1185.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1181.52,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"That came from this email and it was assigned to Jessica.","index":343,"end_time":1191.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1185.82,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":344,"end_time":1192.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1191.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And Justin, so this is an activity report, essentially.","index":345,"end_time":1196.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1192.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s what''s telling us if they were.","index":346,"end_time":1198.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1196.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"MQL or not, correct?","index":347,"end_time":1200.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1198.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yes.","index":348,"end_time":1200.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1200.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":349,"end_time":1200.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1200.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And is.","index":350,"end_time":1201.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1201.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know there''s the manual process, right.","index":351,"end_time":1204.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1202.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Where they convert to an MQL, the sales team and those are the BDRs.","index":352,"end_time":1210.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1204.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is that right?","index":353,"end_time":1210.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1210.06,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That would do that or.","index":354,"end_time":1212.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1211.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No.","index":355,"end_time":1212.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1212.07,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"To create an mql, they can fill out a form on the website and it''ll create it.","index":356,"end_time":1218.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1213.99,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"The form is like a Marketo form.","index":357,"end_time":1221.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1220.07,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"We''ll call the lead input form.","index":358,"end_time":1224.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1222.71,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"If it''s not just BDRs, it''ll be salespeople from AQI Hawk.","index":359,"end_time":1228.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1224.03,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"I think Hydromet can also needs for aqi.","index":360,"end_time":1231.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1228.11,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":361,"end_time":1232.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1232.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Those go in as people records in Marketo first though.","index":362,"end_time":1236.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1232.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":363,"end_time":1236.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1236.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then do.","index":364,"end_time":1238.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1237.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Do they put.","index":365,"end_time":1239.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1238.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"They flow.","index":366,"end_time":1240.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1239.61,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The exact same way.","index":367,"end_time":1243.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1242.41,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"They''ll be called hand raised because they.","index":368,"end_time":1245.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1243.45,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Work through a form on the website.","index":369,"end_time":1247.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1245.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":370,"end_time":1248.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1247.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I will just say the person''s name that filled out the form instead of the tactic.","index":371,"end_time":1253.129,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1248.33,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":372,"end_time":1255.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1254.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And they''ll come over as contact records or lead records.","index":373,"end_time":1259.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1255.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Depends if we already knew about them and they''re already in Marketa''s.","index":374,"end_time":1262.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1259.69,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Data or Salesforce database, then there''ll be contacts.","index":375,"end_time":1265.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1262.73,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"But if they''re totally new, like let''s say Hawk had a new customer, they wanted to sell AQI software for it.","index":376,"end_time":1270.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1265.05,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"They would submit it through the lead it perform that''s totally new to AQI''s database.","index":377,"end_time":1275.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1271.19,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"They''ll come in as a lead and the MQL will be attached to the lead.","index":378,"end_time":1278.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1275.55,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"It''s only the time that you click on this Create opportunity or Convert lead that it changes them from the lead to the contact.","index":379,"end_time":1284.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1278.71,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":380,"end_time":1285.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1284.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So if they do fill out a form, the marketo form, it comes over as a lead.","index":381,"end_time":1290.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1285.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let''s say they didn''t exist.","index":382,"end_time":1291.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1290.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, it''s a brand new person.","index":383,"end_time":1292.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1291.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":384,"end_time":1293.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1292.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So they would come over as a lead object in Salesforce.","index":385,"end_time":1296.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1293.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The BDR would would have to manually go in and say convert lead so that they.","index":386,"end_time":1302.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1297.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, they click this button and it converts the lead to contact.","index":387,"end_time":1305.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1302.33,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"The BDR will have to create an account for that or attach them to an existing account if they already have one.","index":388,"end_time":1311.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1305.73,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Because it could be a new person for an existing account.","index":389,"end_time":1313.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1311.37,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And then it creates an opportunity.","index":390,"end_time":1316.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1315.09,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And it all does that with this one button.","index":391,"end_time":1319.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1316.53,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"If the person''s already a contact because they existed before, maybe they like we tried to sell them, they didn''t want to buy, they came back a year later, they would click Create Opportunity.","index":392,"end_time":1328.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1319.57,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"So in this case, it''s still going to close up this mql, it''s going to say qualified.","index":393,"end_time":1335.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1329.07,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"You''d have to set the stage.","index":394,"end_time":1337.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1336.11,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"I think it''s one of one of.","index":395,"end_time":1341.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1337.47,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"The things down here.","index":396,"end_time":1342.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1341.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Or maybe I don''t have access to them all, but oh, it''ll be status.","index":397,"end_time":1346.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1342.99,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Instead of working.","index":398,"end_time":1346.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1346.07,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"It''ll say qualified.","index":399,"end_time":1347.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1346.59,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And when you go to create the Opportunity, it forces you to pick that status first.","index":400,"end_time":1351.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1348.83,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"And then it''ll create an opportunity, attach it to an existing contact.","index":401,"end_time":1355.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1352.27,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"So this one''s for existing contacts, this one''s for new leads.","index":402,"end_time":1359.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1355.95,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":403,"end_time":1362.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1361.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And.","index":404,"end_time":1363.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1363.49,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Is the MQL date populated at that time?","index":405,"end_time":1369.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1365.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because there are like MQL date fields.","index":406,"end_time":1371.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1369.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Does that get automatically populated at conversion or.","index":407,"end_time":1375.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1371.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s a Maria or Kyle question.","index":408,"end_time":1377.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1375.89,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"I think it was developed by a Salesforce developer we hired.","index":409,"end_time":1380.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1377.57,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s done.","index":410,"end_time":1384.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1383.58,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"It''s done somewhere in a maze of Apex that is not documented.","index":411,"end_time":1390.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1386.7,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So we are not sure.","index":412,"end_time":1393.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1391.26,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Please don''t use this process for your new.","index":413,"end_time":1396.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1394.06,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Your HubSpot integration.","index":414,"end_time":1397.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1396.46,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Yeah, I would even say you can just ignore everything that''s going on here and build what is best practice.","index":415,"end_time":1404.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1398.06,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah, this helps me out a lot.","index":416,"end_time":1406.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1404.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I appreciate it.","index":417,"end_time":1407.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1406.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because we''ve been going down the rabbit hole of.","index":418,"end_time":1412.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1407.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Of different contacts and such which.","index":419,"end_time":1414.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1412.61,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Which leads me to one question.","index":420,"end_time":1416.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1414.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I didn''t want to do anything.","index":421,"end_time":1417.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1416.61,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I created some views for our team.","index":422,"end_time":1419.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1417.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But I was wondering how you all feel about us creating some test contacts just so we can see how something goes from Marketo.","index":423,"end_time":1428.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1419.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like I literally want to look at different fields, see how they behave.","index":424,"end_time":1432.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1428.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I can convert something I want to see like which date fields might get triggered sometimes, you know, without documentation, there''s really no way to do it unless.","index":425,"end_time":1440.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1432.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We do some test contacts and flow through.","index":426,"end_time":1442.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1440.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But I didn''t want to do any.","index":427,"end_time":1443.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1442.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Of that until I talked with you all.","index":428,"end_time":1445.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1443.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, on the Salesforce end you can totally do that.","index":429,"end_time":1450.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1447.66,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"The only thing that we would be wary of is if you create an opportunity, don''t move it past generate prospect.","index":430,"end_time":1458.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1450.46,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Other than that, go crazy.","index":431,"end_time":1463.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1461.1,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Maybe include the name test in the name of the contact so that the BDRs don''t accidentally try to contact this person.","index":432,"end_time":1469.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1463.89,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"But you could definitely make some test contacts.","index":433,"end_time":1473.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1470.69,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"I believe there''s even.","index":434,"end_time":1475.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1474.05,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Kyle, you have a test account, right?","index":435,"end_time":1476.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1475.05,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"It might be good to put it on your test account.","index":436,"end_time":1478.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1476.61,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah, there is one.","index":437,"end_time":1480.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1479.97,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"I''ll get the link to that.","index":438,"end_time":1482.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1480.85,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Let me go back to my agenda here.","index":439,"end_time":1488.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1486.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"See.","index":440,"end_time":1489.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1489.17,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Didn''t see get MQL this year.","index":441,"end_time":1502.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1500.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So MQL report.","index":442,"end_time":1503.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1502.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That helps.","index":443,"end_time":1504.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1503.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I''ll go back and look at that screen and.","index":444,"end_time":1506.499,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1504.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And.","index":445,"end_time":1506.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1506.499,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"See you got lost in translation.","index":446,"end_time":1512.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1510.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":447,"end_time":1514.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1514.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":448,"end_time":1514.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1514.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this is also like just a big question.","index":449,"end_time":1516.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1514.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Methodology wise.","index":450,"end_time":1519.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1518.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"When we go to do a migration, I''ll just open it up to you all.","index":451,"end_time":1522.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1519.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So try to figure out like the.","index":452,"end_time":1523.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1522.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The source of truth for.","index":453,"end_time":1526.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1524.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"For contact records.","index":454,"end_time":1527.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1526.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So when we do go to HubSpot, I''m wondering if we use Salesforce as the base of the data that we then clean and and Sync to from HubSpot to Salesforce.","index":455,"end_time":1539.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1527.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Or do we start with Marketo people records and go in that.","index":456,"end_time":1543.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1539.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like how do you all think about like the latest and greatest the source of truth?","index":457,"end_time":1548.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1543.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If we are migrating data to a new environment.","index":458,"end_time":1552.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1549.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I would say we definitely want some of the Salesforce stuff.","index":459,"end_time":1562.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1559.1,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"I would say kind of how it works is like we have stuff in Salesforce that Marketo might not have because we''ve done like an upload and stuff of different contexts, but Marketo will have stuff that Salesforce doesn''t have because maybe they haven''t hit their lead score yet or something went wrong with the integration.","index":460,"end_time":1580.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1562.34,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So I would almost say if you have the resources to do both Marketo and Salesforce with like some kind of deduplication that Would be great if like we had to pick one.","index":461,"end_time":1594.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1580.89,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"I would pick Salesforce, but I am incredibly biased.","index":462,"end_time":1598.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1594.81,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So.","index":463,"end_time":1598.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1598.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No, no, I would say Salesforce too.","index":464,"end_time":1600.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1598.77,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":465,"end_time":1601.55,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1601.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And like 98% of Marketo will be in Salesforce.","index":466,"end_time":1604.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1601.55,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"It''s just if it''s missing like an important field like company or first or last name or one of email or phone number because those are the requirements to sync to Salesforce.","index":467,"end_time":1615.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1604.47,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"But that would only be a small, small percentage of the, the database in Marketo and those people are probably not getting contact anytime soon anyway because we don''t have that information and it''s kind of crucial.","index":468,"end_time":1629.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1615.39,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"But like Maria said, there''s.","index":469,"end_time":1633.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1631.75,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"There''s going to be a lot of folks in Salesforce that are not in Marketo because we pay for contact to Marketo and if that person''s inactive, we clear them out after, you know, eight or ten months or so due to an activity.","index":470,"end_time":1643.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1633.47,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"We don''t keep them in there but we don''t delete them from Salesforce because they could still be useful.","index":471,"end_time":1647.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1643.99,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, so that''s the other question.","index":472,"end_time":1649.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1648.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So you delete them from Marketo and there''s not.","index":473,"end_time":1652.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1649.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because with HubSpot there''s a two way sync and we can define rules as to if it''s not in one environment, what happens.","index":474,"end_time":1660.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1653.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it sounds like if you do delete it out of Marketo it remains in Salesforce for record keeping purposes.","index":475,"end_time":1669.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1661.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so is that, would you like that same functionality?","index":476,"end_time":1673.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1669.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Basically Salesforce will not get updated from, you know, there won''t be a push from HubSpot if we delete a record, is that you would like to mirror that functionality.","index":477,"end_time":1683.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1673.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Just to repeat back what you said.","index":478,"end_time":1688.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1686.11,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Basically if you delete something in HubSpot it gets, it does not get deleted in Salesforce and vice versa.","index":479,"end_time":1694.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1688.11,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"There''s flexibility with the two way sync.","index":480,"end_time":1697.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1694.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You could, you can have rules that say, you know, essentially you''re defining like what is the source of truth.","index":481,"end_time":1704.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1697.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then if one environment deletes a record, which one takes precedent.","index":482,"end_time":1711.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1704.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So for example, if we say Salesforce is the source of truth and you know, if we delete a record in HubSpot, say, you know, a contact record that is out of HubSpot but that would not send an update over to Salesforce and say delete it over there as well.","index":483,"end_time":1730.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1711.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Now if we delete something from Salesforce though, we could define it and say yes, please delete it out of HubSpot as well.","index":484,"end_time":1736.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1730.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So there''s kind of that, you know, hierarchy that we would define as to.","index":485,"end_time":1742.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1736.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What that rule is.","index":486,"end_time":1742.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1742.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And we''re flexible.","index":487,"end_time":1744.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1742.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, every business is different.","index":488,"end_time":1746.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1744.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It depends on like where the.","index":489,"end_time":1747.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1746.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The source of truth exists.","index":490,"end_time":1750.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1748.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So what would be the use case of someone deleting a contact in HubSpot?","index":491,"end_time":1755.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1751.71,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Let''s say that the email bounces and just not a valid record.","index":492,"end_time":1761.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1758.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And.","index":493,"end_time":1762.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1762.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean you could, you could move it to a non marketing contact, but then it''s just like a dormant.","index":494,"end_time":1770.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1765.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s stale data.","index":495,"end_time":1773.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1771.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so that''s one way maybe you.","index":496,"end_time":1778.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1773.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s there.","index":497,"end_time":1779.399,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1778.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There''s an error.","index":498,"end_time":1780.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1779.399,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So put in the wrong email address and there''s a duplicate record that already exists.","index":499,"end_time":1784.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1780.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So like maybe you spelled the name incorrectly on the email.","index":500,"end_time":1787.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1784.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It was a manual entry.","index":501,"end_time":1789.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1788.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You want to delete it out of HubSpot that already exists.","index":502,"end_time":1792.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1789.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s.","index":503,"end_time":1793.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1792.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Those are a couple that come to mind.","index":504,"end_time":1794.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1793.06,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":505,"end_time":1795.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1795.46,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"I would say then we would probably want it to flow in because we want the like the sellers.","index":506,"end_time":1801.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1795.86,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"The goal is for the sellers to stay in one place the whole time.","index":507,"end_time":1804.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1802.1,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"But the BDRs are going to be the ones who live in kind of have one foot in both worlds.","index":508,"end_time":1809.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1804.74,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"And if they''re cleaning up a contact, I would want that to flow into Salesforce so there''s not just a bunch of like dead contacts floating around Salesforce that like are useless.","index":509,"end_time":1822.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1810.42,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So I think it makes sense to sync if you delete it in Salesforce deleted in HubSpot.","index":510,"end_time":1825.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1822.14,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"If you didn''t HubSpot deleted in Salesforce.","index":511,"end_time":1827.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1825.9,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"This way it keeps the two systems in sync and lowers the amount of administrative work that the BDR team has to do.","index":512,"end_time":1834.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1828.3,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":513,"end_time":1834.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1834.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, that works.","index":514,"end_time":1837.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1835.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Maria, real quick though.","index":515,"end_time":1840.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1839.66,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Is there ever a world where like the rep would enter in a contact and then that would sink into HubSpot and then with the BDR or someone in marketing action that context say actually this is not a good contact and then delete it which would then delete it in Salesforce without maybe the.","index":516,"end_time":1857.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1840.86,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"So.","index":517,"end_time":1858.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1858.47,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Yes, but also if they''re deciding what''s a good contact and what''s not based on like if the email is bouncing or they can''t get ahold of someone or someone doesn''t have a last name, then maybe that contact should be deleted and the rep should have to input the right information.","index":518,"end_time":1875.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1859.75,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"You know, but if there''s a process where they''re deleting stuff other than deleting bad data, then I.","index":519,"end_time":1884.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1877.84,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Then I think we should talk about it more.","index":520,"end_time":1886.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1884.88,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"But if it''s just because bad data.","index":521,"end_time":1887.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1886.28,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah, I think bad data.","index":522,"end_time":1890.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1888.88,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"I think my only hesitation would be like the world of like we can''t get in contact with them?","index":523,"end_time":1894.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1890.48,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Right.","index":524,"end_time":1895.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1895.2,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Like maybe marketing can''t get in contact with them, but maybe the sales rep has a relationship with that person.","index":525,"end_time":1900.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1895.52,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"We probably wouldn''t want to delete that one.","index":526,"end_time":1902.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1901.2,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"But.","index":527,"end_time":1903.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1903.43,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"So if, if they''re reaching out, if like marketing is reaching out to someone and they get no response, are they deleting that contact?","index":528,"end_time":1912.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1903.67,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Probably.","index":529,"end_time":1917.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1917.27,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"A question for Barb or Tristan, I would think.","index":530,"end_time":1919.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1917.63,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Like what would be like a use case for that?","index":531,"end_time":1921.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1919.83,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Like let''s say they reach out 20 times and they''re getting nothing but dead air.","index":532,"end_time":1925.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1921.51,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Do they delete that contact or do they just mark that as like this person''s non responsive?","index":533,"end_time":1931.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1925.99,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a good question.","index":534,"end_time":1934.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1933.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Barb can answer too, but I think that''s more of like a business process.","index":535,"end_time":1938.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1934.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like is there a period of time that like HubSpot will do that automatically?","index":536,"end_time":1943.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1938.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''ll like, if folks haven''t even replied or opened an email or done any engagement, they''ll move to non marketing contact.","index":537,"end_time":1950.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1943.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That just prevents those folks from getting into like custom audiences on the paid side and stuff like that.","index":538,"end_time":1956.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1950.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There, there''s something that you could do where maybe you go and enrich those contacts separately, you know, and see if those emails are valid.","index":539,"end_time":1966.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1959.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You can do some research.","index":540,"end_time":1967.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1966.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like is that person still in the same role?","index":541,"end_time":1968.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1967.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So there''s some automation that we can do there.","index":542,"end_time":1972,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1968.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then if, if they don''t meet certain criteria, then yeah, you could delete them out of the database and just clean those up.","index":543,"end_time":1978.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1972,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That would be something I think you would do like every quarter, maybe even every year, depending on what the volume is.","index":544,"end_time":1985.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1979.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that would just be my only hesitation.","index":545,"end_time":1989.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1988.07,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"I think what Maria said about deleting contacts makes sense.","index":546,"end_time":1992.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1989.91,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"I just think that if the only reason we''d be deleting a contact is because they''re not responding to us, I think that''s where I would hesitate and maybe pause on that just because I know like for our sales rep.","index":547,"end_time":2002.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1992.27,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Right.","index":548,"end_time":2002.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2002.59,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"For Salesforce, I respond to my Salesforce rep.","index":549,"end_time":2005.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2002.87,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"But you know, when I go do a Salesforce demo, I don''t respond to the slew of other Salesforce reps that come knocking on my door.","index":550,"end_time":2011.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2005.07,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"And I may look like I''m inactive, but in reality I''m just not responding to that person.","index":551,"end_time":2015.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2011.47,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":552,"end_time":2017.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2015.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I think the deleting thing, that''s more of like an educator.","index":553,"end_time":2019.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2017.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I don''t even think that''s a, like a huge.","index":554,"end_time":2021.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2019.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There won''t be a lot of volumes of, of deletions I wouldn''t imagine.","index":555,"end_time":2026.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2023.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But it''s more about like the, the rules that we Put in place and how data flows and essentially, like, which.","index":556,"end_time":2032.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2026.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Which system overrides?","index":557,"end_time":2034.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2032.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Which is the big question there.","index":558,"end_time":2036.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2034.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And if you all.","index":559,"end_time":2038.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2038.07,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know Justin jumped off, but I have some salesforce just field questions.","index":560,"end_time":2043.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2038.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I have a contact pulled up.","index":561,"end_time":2045.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2043.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If I can share my screen real quick.","index":562,"end_time":2047.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2045.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I just wanted to go through.","index":563,"end_time":2051.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2049.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this is a recent lead that was created.","index":564,"end_time":2055,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2051.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It was from.","index":565,"end_time":2057.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2056.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, came through Marketo.","index":566,"end_time":2059.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2057.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so it''s a lead.","index":567,"end_time":2061.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2060.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It comes in as open, not contacted.","index":568,"end_time":2064.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2062.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so I was wondering, like, there''s some other steps here, like what.","index":569,"end_time":2069.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2064.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What would typically happen with this lead?","index":570,"end_time":2073.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2070.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because I think it was.","index":571,"end_time":2075.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2074.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":572,"end_time":2077.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2076.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this is from a Hawk upload, I''m guessing, but yeah, like, tell me, like, what happens in this list here?","index":573,"end_time":2086.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2077.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What does a BDR do?","index":574,"end_time":2089.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2087.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like what.","index":575,"end_time":2090.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2089.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This is like a very fresh lead, right, that just got created.","index":576,"end_time":2093.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2090.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like what happens next to here?","index":577,"end_time":2094.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2093.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, Maria, correct me if I''m wrong, but I think for the most part the BDRs are primarily just working out that task and this lead, they may be clicking into it to get, like, contact information, but other than that, it''s kind of just a placeholder in a sense until it gets converted, basically.","index":578,"end_time":2114.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2095.71,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Okay.","index":579,"end_time":2116.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2115.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And Kyle, So this got created on the 6th.","index":580,"end_time":2118.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2116.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So yesterday.","index":581,"end_time":2119.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2118.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then Blake has a.","index":582,"end_time":2121.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2119.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"A task a couple days out.","index":583,"end_time":2124.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2121.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so what is.","index":584,"end_time":2126.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2125.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What is Blake doing with.","index":585,"end_time":2128.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2127.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"With that task?","index":586,"end_time":2129.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2128.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Research to figure out if it goes to another stage or.","index":587,"end_time":2134.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2130.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":588,"end_time":2135.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2134.76,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"So like, the, The.","index":589,"end_time":2136.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2135.16,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"The task date is basically the date that I believe he would be actioning this lead to say, okay, here we have a lead.","index":590,"end_time":2142.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2136.28,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Is this a viable, you know, a viable lead to be turned into an opportunity for the rep into action.","index":591,"end_time":2149.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2142.52,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"But Maria.","index":592,"end_time":2150.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2149.57,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Yeah, so that is actually the due date for him.","index":593,"end_time":2153.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2150.85,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Oh, that''s the due date that they''re showing there.","index":594,"end_time":2155.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2153.85,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":595,"end_time":2156.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2155.73,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"If he.","index":596,"end_time":2156.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2156.09,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"It takes him longer than November 11, it shows up as late and like, that''s an issue.","index":597,"end_time":2160.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2156.37,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So ideally, he''s responding to them as fast as he can, but we''ve got one BDR and let''s say one day we get a million inbound leads and it''s like.","index":598,"end_time":2169.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2160.85,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So he.","index":599,"end_time":2172.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2171.01,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"He doesn''t do anything on this lead record and he actually does not change this stage.","index":600,"end_time":2178.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2173.9,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"That pipeline you see at the top at all.","index":601,"end_time":2181.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2179.18,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"The only thing that happens here is if he converts it, the automation will set this lead to converted.","index":602,"end_time":2190.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2181.02,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So if you go into the lead, I can kind of show you what his workflow looks like if you click on that task or the lead task.","index":603,"end_time":2200.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2192.3,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":604,"end_time":2202.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2200.47,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":605,"end_time":2203.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2203.11,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So he puts in his contact attempt date for number one, then number two, and number Three.","index":606,"end_time":2209.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2203.59,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So he attempts to contact them three separate times.","index":607,"end_time":2211.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2209.31,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"And this is where he fills out all this stuff.","index":608,"end_time":2215.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2213.59,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So the bant information, they figure out he would update more statuses here.","index":609,"end_time":2221.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2215.75,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Like see where it says MQL status.","index":610,"end_time":2223.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2221.67,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"New.","index":611,"end_time":2223.83,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2223.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"If he wants to remove it.","index":612,"end_time":2226.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2225.84,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Like, this is where he.","index":613,"end_time":2228.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2226.96,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Where they like live and breathe.","index":614,"end_time":2230.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2228.72,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"And I keep saying he because it''s just Blake right now.","index":615,"end_time":2232.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2230.44,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":616,"end_time":2232.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2232.4,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"But if you scroll down a little further, see where it says qualification source.","index":617,"end_time":2240.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2232.8,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Qualification source details.","index":618,"end_time":2241.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2240.28,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"And then there should be qualification notes somewhere.","index":619,"end_time":2244.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2241.64,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Maybe I''m wrong.","index":620,"end_time":2245.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2244.72,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Maybe it''s up a little further.","index":621,"end_time":2246.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2245.48,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Let''s see if they''re.","index":622,"end_time":2248.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2247.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, here you go.","index":623,"end_time":2250.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2249.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Notes.","index":624,"end_time":2252.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2252.32,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"That''s what flows when he.","index":625,"end_time":2254.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2252.68,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"When he''s like, hey, this should be an op.","index":626,"end_time":2256.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2254.52,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"I''m going to hand it off to a seller.","index":627,"end_time":2258.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2256.96,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"He converts it into an opportunity.","index":628,"end_time":2261.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2259.2,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"He puts his notes in this qualification notes and those get pulled into the opportunity.","index":629,"end_time":2267.199,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2261.28,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"And that field is where we''re doing a lot of reporting.","index":630,"end_time":2272,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2268.08,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So like, if it''s a direct flip.","index":631,"end_time":2273.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2272,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"We talked about that last time.","index":632,"end_time":2275.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2273.76,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"He puts direct flip in this field and when he converts it, it pastes itself on the opportunity.","index":633,"end_time":2281.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2275.92,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":634,"end_time":2283.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2282.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it''s a free form field that we''re adding a lot of just details in there.","index":635,"end_time":2286.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2283.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And that''s.","index":636,"end_time":2287.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2286.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, we''d love to not do that anymore, so.","index":637,"end_time":2290.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2287.99,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"But yeah, that''s what''s.","index":638,"end_time":2291.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2290.55,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"What today''s status is.","index":639,"end_time":2293.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2291.71,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So he''s like literally not touching the lead object.","index":640,"end_time":2295.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2293.15,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"He''s just living in the task and referencing the lead object.","index":641,"end_time":2299.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2296.23,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Okay.","index":642,"end_time":2300.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2299.67,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"And then this gets printed on the.","index":643,"end_time":2301.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2300.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The opportunity record.","index":644,"end_time":2303.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2301.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Sounds like the qualifier qualification notes is what really drives that in.","index":645,"end_time":2310.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2303.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Marie, when you say you''re reporting off of that, what does that look like?","index":646,"end_time":2314.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2310.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is there a certain report that you all are using or.","index":647,"end_time":2316.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2314.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There''s a bunch of reports, but both basically.","index":648,"end_time":2320.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2317.7,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"The biggest one is like those direct flips where they put direct flip all caps.","index":649,"end_time":2327.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2321.06,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"And we can filter those out or filter those in.","index":650,"end_time":2330.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2327.86,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"This is a hawk lead, which basically what this is is our one like our Dotted Line parent company.","index":651,"end_time":2340.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2331.51,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":652,"end_time":2340.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2340.15,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"They''re not like officially a parent company, but they kind of are.","index":653,"end_time":2342.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2340.47,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah, I like dotted line.","index":654,"end_time":2344.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2342.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s.","index":655,"end_time":2344.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2344.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s it.","index":656,"end_time":2345.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2344.99,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"I like it.","index":657,"end_time":2345.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2345.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, our Dotted Line parent company, they have sales reps who have a ton of customers and they refer people to us and this is them filling out a form.","index":658,"end_time":2358.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2346.39,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"They say, hey, this person''s.","index":659,"end_time":2361.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2359.56,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"This person could be interested.","index":660,"end_time":2362.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2361.04,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"And then the BDR reaches out to this person and he''ll put hawk lead information in this qualified notes as well.","index":661,"end_time":2370.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2363.32,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So that''s also like a keyword that we use.","index":662,"end_time":2372.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2370.52,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So anything, basically it says qualification in front of it is what we''re using for reporting.","index":663,"end_time":2381.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2375.24,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":664,"end_time":2382.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2382.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And some other things here, like qualification source.","index":665,"end_time":2385.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2382.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":666,"end_time":2386.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2386.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Anything else that jumps out?","index":667,"end_time":2387.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2386.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean, this is a free form field.","index":668,"end_time":2389.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2387.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Are there any fields that you''re reporting off of or the.","index":669,"end_time":2395.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2389.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The drive decisions downstream?","index":670,"end_time":2397.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2395.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So, like, there''s sales requests here.","index":671,"end_time":2398.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2397.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What are the options even?","index":672,"end_time":2399.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2398.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, the qualifications ones.","index":673,"end_time":2405.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2403.12,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Do generated by.","index":674,"end_time":2407.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2405.28,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Does generated by is relatively important because it will help us understand what hawk seller needs to get paid.","index":675,"end_time":2417.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2407.16,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So we have like a spiff for hawk that basically, like, hey, you send us a person, they turn into a qualified opportunity and