,"index":736,"end_time":2575.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2574.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And this is a customer support feed.","index":737,"end_time":2578.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2576.7,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Which basically means the customer support team has indicated that this customer would be game for an upsell.","index":738,"end_time":2586.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2578.7,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So they send it into Blake.","index":739,"end_time":2588.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2587.1,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Blake says, great, I''ll turn it into an up for the csm.","index":740,"end_time":2591.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2588.46,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"And then he moves on with his life.","index":741,"end_time":2592.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2591.1,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Okay, so direct flip means, like, Blake''s not really qualifying at all.","index":742,"end_time":2599.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2594.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We already know that it''s an opportunity.","index":743,"end_time":2602.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2599.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it just kind of zooms through.","index":744,"end_time":2603.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2602.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, pretty much.","index":745,"end_time":2605.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2604.53,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Like, we could set up automation.","index":746,"end_time":2606.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2605.25,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"If we could set up automation for this, the BDR team would love you forever because they don''t get paid on this.","index":747,"end_time":2613.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2607.01,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"It''s a waste of their time.","index":748,"end_time":2614.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2613.17,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"But someone has to do it.","index":749,"end_time":2616.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2615.25,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"And that someone is them right now.","index":750,"end_time":2617.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2616.41,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":751,"end_time":2618.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2618.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so the only thing that we know, Direct flip is literally in the qualification notes field.","index":752,"end_time":2623.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2618.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There''s.","index":753,"end_time":2623.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2623.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There''s not like a checkbox or anything like that that, that we would report on.","index":754,"end_time":2627.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2623.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":755,"end_time":2627.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2627.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Nope.","index":756,"end_time":2628.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2628.14,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"But we could definitely.","index":757,"end_time":2629.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2628.62,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"We would love to change that.","index":758,"end_time":2630.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2629.46,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So.","index":759,"end_time":2631.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2630.62,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":760,"end_time":2631.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2631.18,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"And.","index":761,"end_time":2631.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2631.62,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"And that prior link I sent is to Blake''s VC report.","index":762,"end_time":2636.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2631.98,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"And you''ll see in that report, like in the filters that he''s filtering out on ops that have.","index":763,"end_time":2642.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2636.78,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Basically it contains qualification of direct flip.","index":764,"end_time":2646.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2642.62,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"So, yeah, if you click on the funnel icon top right of the report and then right there all the way at the bottom.","index":765,"end_time":2652.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2646.62,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Right.","index":766,"end_time":2653.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2653.02,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Like, that is our very scientific approach.","index":767,"end_time":2657.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2653.34,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Got it.","index":768,"end_time":2658.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2657.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No, well, this stuff''s important.","index":769,"end_time":2659.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2658.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":770,"end_time":2659.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2659.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because you always.","index":771,"end_time":2660.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2659.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All it takes is like one field or something to drive a whole report.","index":772,"end_time":2664.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2660.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so.","index":773,"end_time":2665.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2664.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, so we''re just searching for direct flip.","index":774,"end_time":2667.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2665.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":775,"end_time":2672.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2671.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Something else that''s really valuable for this report.","index":776,"end_time":2674.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2672.35,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"If you look at the funnel, see how it says old value is generate prospect, and the new value is not closed loss or generate prospect.","index":777,"end_time":2682.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2674.75,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"This is what I was kind of talking before about, like the MQL thing.","index":778,"end_time":2686.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2683.11,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Like, they will.","index":779,"end_time":2687.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2686.63,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"When they make a opportunity, they make it and generate prospect, then the seller will reach out.","index":780,"end_time":2693.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2688.23,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"And if the seller decides, like, yeah, this is like, he''s correct.","index":781,"end_time":2696.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2693.23,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"This is an op that, like, people are interested in and I can sell to.","index":782,"end_time":2702.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2696.36,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"They''ll move it up to qualify, and that counts as now it''s a sales qualified lead, but in a.","index":783,"end_time":2709,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2702.08,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"An opportunity and generate prospect is not a sales qualified lead yet.","index":784,"end_time":2712.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2709,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":785,"end_time":2714.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2713.36,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":786,"end_time":2716,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2715.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Walk me through.","index":787,"end_time":2716.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2716,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So old value is literally what.","index":788,"end_time":2720.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2716.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What is that the old value of?","index":789,"end_time":2722.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2720.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this, this is just an opportunity field history report.","index":790,"end_time":2727.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2723.98,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So I wouldn''t worry too much about it.","index":791,"end_time":2729.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2727.9,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Basically, it''s something that takes a snapshot of certain fields in an opportunity when an event occurs.","index":792,"end_time":2736.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2729.5,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So this is saying, okay, when the stage has changed and it goes from generate prospect to something else.","index":793,"end_time":2745.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2736.7,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Listen.","index":794,"end_time":2747.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2746.62,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Oh, this is.","index":795,"end_time":2747.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2747.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, I got you.","index":796,"end_time":2748.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2747.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So the value changed from one to the other.","index":797,"end_time":2751.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2749.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Take a.","index":798,"end_time":2751.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2751.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Basically a stamp of.","index":799,"end_time":2752.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2751.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Of what the fields were at that time.","index":800,"end_time":2755.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2752.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yes.","index":801,"end_time":2755.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2755.28,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So that''s.","index":802,"end_time":2756.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2755.84,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"That''s also kind of important to our business processes is a way to have the BDR team hand something to sales and then have sales say, yes, this is qualified, or no, go like, no, get rid of this.","index":803,"end_time":2768.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2756.4,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Okay, got that.","index":804,"end_time":2770.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2769.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, so I guess generate prospect is kind of in a limbo world because it''s not.","index":805,"end_time":2777.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2772.16,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Sales hasn''t qualified it yet, but marketing has qualified it.","index":806,"end_time":2781.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2777.52,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So.","index":807,"end_time":2783.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2783.28,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, but this is at the opportunity level, like, record.","index":808,"end_time":2787.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2783.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So are you looking at.","index":809,"end_time":2790.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2788.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So generate prospect, the old value.","index":810,"end_time":2795.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2792.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That is.","index":811,"end_time":2796,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2795.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And that old.","index":812,"end_time":2799.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2799.04,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"That.","index":813,"end_time":2799.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2799.68,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Right.","index":814,"end_time":2800.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2799.88,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Like, that is the opportunity stage.","index":815,"end_time":2801.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2800.04,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Opportunity stage of old value.","index":816,"end_time":2803.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2802.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":817,"end_time":2804.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2803.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":818,"end_time":2804.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2804.39,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Okay.","index":819,"end_time":2805.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2805.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, good.","index":820,"end_time":2811.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2810.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this helps.","index":821,"end_time":2811.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2811.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''m going to save some of these.","index":822,"end_time":2814.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2812.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":823,"end_time":2815.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2814.71,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Any other reports that you feel like folks are, like, really looking at, like, every day or every week?","index":824,"end_time":2821.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2815.07,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It seems like this is a pretty big one.","index":825,"end_time":2823.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2821.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What else jumps out at you that, you know, folks are relying on?","index":826,"end_time":2828.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2824.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''m trying to find.","index":827,"end_time":2829.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2828.83,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Barb, do you know what dashboard they created for, like, their daily.","index":828,"end_time":2836.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2829.59,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Their daily huddle or their weekly huddle that they''re doing?","index":829,"end_time":2838.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2836.51,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"I''m trying to see if I can find that one.","index":830,"end_time":2840.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2838.83,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":831,"end_time":2842.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2842.27,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Any reports tied to Daily Visual Management?","index":832,"end_time":2845.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2842.87,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"It''s called Kyle.","index":833,"end_time":2846.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2845.23,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m trying to see.","index":834,"end_time":2847.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2846.59,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"I do have it.","index":835,"end_time":2848.59,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2847.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll share it.","index":836,"end_time":2849.95,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2848.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I have it.","index":837,"end_time":2850.75,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2850.19,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":838,"end_time":2851.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2850.75,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Is it called Marketing Daily Management 2025?","index":839,"end_time":2853.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2851.07,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"I''ll let you share, Barb, if you have it.","index":840,"end_time":2857.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2855.8,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Yeah, thanks.","index":841,"end_time":2859.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2857.64,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Okay, so this is a. Yeah, so.","index":842,"end_time":2888.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2886.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This is used on a daily basis or on a daily or weekly basis.","index":843,"end_time":2892.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2888.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know they have at least a meeting on Fridays, so it''s at least weekly.","index":844,"end_time":2898.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2894.93,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Barbara.","index":845,"end_time":2898.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2898.33,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":846,"end_time":2899.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2898.73,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Are they.","index":847,"end_time":2899.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2899.01,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Are they meeting daily still or is it just once a week that they''ve switched to.","index":848,"end_time":2903.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2899.37,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Yeah, we meet three times a week, but these reports are done on a Friday.","index":849,"end_time":2908.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2904.21,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And.","index":850,"end_time":2909.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2908.99,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s really bizarre, to tell you the truth.","index":851,"end_time":2912.95,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2910.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So on the MQL that you see on the top left are not the numbers we.","index":852,"end_time":2920.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2912.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We do, I guess, Friday to Thursday.","index":853,"end_time":2925.23,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2920.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Night.","index":854,"end_time":2925.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2925.31,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"On the MQL.","index":855,"end_time":2929.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2928.03,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So what you see right now is 87.","index":856,"end_time":2931.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2929.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"What I reported today was 75.","index":857,"end_time":2933.79,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2931.87,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"There''s a lot of reasons for that, but.","index":858,"end_time":2936.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2934.76,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And so what''s driving.","index":859,"end_time":2941.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2940.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this is an mql.","index":860,"end_time":2943,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2941.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, this is.","index":861,"end_time":2943.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2943,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This is also we were talking about at the beginning.","index":862,"end_time":2946.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2943.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I can go and look at what''s Driving this number.","index":863,"end_time":2949.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2946.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But is that.","index":864,"end_time":2951.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2951.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I have to look at what the report''s pulling.","index":865,"end_time":2957.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2955.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But it''s modified date.","index":866,"end_time":2959.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2957.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":867,"end_time":2963.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2963.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I''ll take a closer look, but this is one of my big questions is like, what.","index":868,"end_time":2967,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2963.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because this is the number you''re reporting on, Barb.","index":869,"end_time":2970.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2968.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This 87.","index":870,"end_time":2971.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2970.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But we need to know what''s.","index":871,"end_time":2972.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2971.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What that''s pulling.","index":872,"end_time":2974.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2973,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I can help with.","index":873,"end_time":2976.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2974.76,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Sorry, just to interject.","index":874,"end_time":2978.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2976.76,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So today when I said that I reported on 20 or 75 versus the 87.","index":875,"end_time":2983.04,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2978.44,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I can tell you why, but go ahead, Maria.","index":876,"end_time":2985.96,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2983.04,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":877,"end_time":2986.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2986.68,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"These are on those tasks, Tristan, that we were looking at, those green tasks that they live on.","index":878,"end_time":2992.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2986.88,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"And it''s colored by.","index":879,"end_time":2993.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2992.6,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah, just the subject.","index":880,"end_time":2995.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2994.04,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"And that''s how they differentiate between the different types.","index":881,"end_time":2998.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2995.28,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Okay, gotcha.","index":882,"end_time":2999.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2998.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it is just the.","index":883,"end_time":3001.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3000.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, the task was modified in a date range.","index":884,"end_time":3005.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3001.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s what we''re saying effectively here, right?","index":885,"end_time":3007.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3005.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Not necessarily.","index":886,"end_time":3012.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3010.6,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"So can you actually go back to the dashboard?","index":887,"end_time":3015,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3012.52,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":888,"end_time":3015.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3015.48,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"And then if you go.","index":889,"end_time":3017,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3016.2,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"You see where the blue text is?","index":890,"end_time":3018.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3017,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"It says, view report MQL for marketing 2025 campaign under basically underneath November.","index":891,"end_time":3023,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3018.16,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":892,"end_time":3023.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3023,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"If you can click on that, then that will give us a holistic view of the report.","index":893,"end_time":3026.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3023.32,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"And then can you click on the funnel icon top?","index":894,"end_time":3031.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3028.76,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Right.","index":895,"end_time":3031.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3031.56,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Right.","index":896,"end_time":3034.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3034.28,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"So, yeah, current year to date.","index":897,"end_time":3036.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3034.68,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Right.","index":898,"end_time":3037.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3037.4,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"And basically this is just looking for tasks that have that subject name that contains marketing quote, qualified lead, and then it''s being grouped by which what you''re seeing is a grouping by creation date.","index":899,"end_time":3049.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3037.76,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Got it.","index":900,"end_time":3052.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3051.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so this is just for FYI purposes, but it''s grouped by creation date by month.","index":901,"end_time":3057.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3052.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":902,"end_time":3058.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3057.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":903,"end_time":3060.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3059.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":904,"end_time":3060.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3060.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This is one of my big questions was how we''re coming to this number and what''s driving that.","index":905,"end_time":3064.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3060.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So this report''s crucial.","index":906,"end_time":3067.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3064.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, got that.","index":907,"end_time":3069.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3067.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, well, report on something.","index":908,"end_time":3075.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3072.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Maybe.","index":909,"end_time":3075.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3075.47,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Maybe it''s relevant for this conversation.","index":910,"end_time":3077.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3075.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But if we can go back to the view that I have to report on.","index":911,"end_time":3082.91,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3077.87,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":912,"end_time":3084.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3084.19,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So if you look at the 87, what I reported on today, it was the Friday to the Thursday.","index":913,"end_time":3091.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3084.55,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":914,"end_time":3091.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3091.07,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s only 75.","index":915,"end_time":3093.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3091.87,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Because what.","index":916,"end_time":3094.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3093.19,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"What is showing in those 87, apparently, MQL, we''ve been.","index":917,"end_time":3099.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3094.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s what we''ve been reporting until I got here.","index":918,"end_time":3102.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3099.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"If I drill down into those, some of them are already opportunities, some of them are support requests.","index":919,"end_time":3109.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3102.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s just anything that filled out a forum or like, not all 87 is my point.","index":920,"end_time":3115.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3109.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They''re not MQL.","index":921,"end_time":3116.95,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3115.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So how do we define them?","index":922,"end_time":3118.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3116.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And so I could not define or defend 87 of them today.","index":923,"end_time":3125,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3118.87,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I could defend 75 maybe.","index":924,"end_time":3127.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3125,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But yeah, that''s, that''s what we''re looking to get help on.","index":925,"end_time":3132.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3128.24,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Kyla Maria.","index":926,"end_time":3134.56,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3133.44,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It just, I, I, that''s my biggest struggle here is that I drill down and says, no, they''re already an opportunity, but we don''t know that in Marketa.","index":927,"end_time":3144.4,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3135.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We, we just count everything as an mql even though they''re already in the system working that lead.","index":928,"end_time":3150.77,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3144.64,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So that''s just something that we have to work on.","index":929,"end_time":3153.97,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3151.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right, does that make sense?","index":930,"end_time":3157.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3155.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It does, yeah.","index":931,"end_time":3159.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3158.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Barb, we''ll get, we''ll get into some of the details too, but this is, this is really helpful for me.","index":932,"end_time":3163.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3159.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Thanks for watching me click around for.","index":933,"end_time":3167.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3163.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"For a bit here in the meeting.","index":934,"end_time":3168.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3167.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But it helped me kind of understand.","index":935,"end_time":3171.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3168.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Some of the key, key data elements.","index":936,"end_time":3173.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3171.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Anything else that you all feel like would be, be helpful.","index":937,"end_time":3176.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3174.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean we got some good reports.","index":938,"end_time":3177.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3176.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That drives a lot of the management reporting.","index":939,"end_time":3182.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3178.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It looks like anything else that you feel like we should check out or that is used heavily.","index":940,"end_time":3188.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3182.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I would say this is probably the most important.","index":941,"end_time":3195.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3191.79,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"But if you could recreate this view in HubSpot without using the custom tasks, that is ideal.","index":942,"end_time":3203.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3196.03,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So like this, having this as a concept is important.","index":943,"end_time":3207.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3204.79,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"The way we''re getting to this, we could very much do without and there are better ways to do it.","index":944,"end_time":3213.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3207.67,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So that''s kind of what I would say as a takeaway.","index":945,"end_time":3217.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3214.63,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":946,"end_time":3219.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3217.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I think that''s a big thing too.","index":947,"end_time":3221.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3219.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And it''s, it''s not even like on the technical side, it''s, it''s even on the business process side too.","index":948,"end_time":3226.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3221.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, you know, how do we define it?","index":949,"end_time":3228.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3226.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then what on the system side, you know, is it an activity, is it a stage, is it a field?","index":950,"end_time":3234.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3228.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because in HubSpot too, like if, you know, as, as we saw here, like when one record changes, there''s a timestamp and so HubSpot will provide that as well for pipeline stages.","index":951,"end_time":3246.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3235.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So yeah, just got to think that through and figure out the, the most efficient way to get the most important data in place for you all.","index":952,"end_time":3254.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3246.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I think the, the big thing for us too is the lead and contact objects in sales.","index":953,"end_time":3264,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3254.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s like a big decision point as well because right now Marketa is pushing people records to lead and then there''s a manual process in Salesforce to convert, you know, at that point.","index":954,"end_time":3275.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3264,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so HubSpot does have lead and contact objects, but leads is used in the sales module.","index":955,"end_time":3280.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3275.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we, we have really a contact record which is similar to Marketo.","index":956,"end_time":3284.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3280.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":957,"end_time":3284.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3284.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There''s not like a, a conversion that has to Happen.","index":958,"end_time":3287.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3284.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But I, as I think through, I''m not sure you got to think about like creating the, the lead first because, you know, in HubSpot there''s going to be a natural connection to an account already.","index":959,"end_time":3300.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3288.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so like, a lot of that doesn''t have to be done manually.","index":960,"end_time":3303.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3300.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So those are some of the things we''re thinking about we''ll have to, to map out.","index":961,"end_time":3308.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3303.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But I think, you know, we got some, some, some good information here today.","index":962,"end_time":3313.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3308.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Thanks for, for jumping on again and walking us through.","index":963,"end_time":3316.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3313.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, totally.","index":964,"end_time":3318.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3317.58,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"You guys definitely have your work cut out for you.","index":965,"end_time":3320.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3318.34,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So have, have a good time.","index":966,"end_time":3321.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3320.22,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"We see all kinds of stuff though.","index":967,"end_time":3324.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3322.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, Kyle and I are working on a, a bank in, in New York City.","index":968,"end_time":3327.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3324.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''re doing something similar where they''re, they''re coming, you know, they''re doing a HubSpot to, to Salesforce migration from, from an old core system.","index":969,"end_time":3337.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3327.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So, um, we see a lot of.","index":970,"end_time":3339.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3337.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"A lot of different things, but it''s fun.","index":971,"end_time":3342.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3339.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll, we''ll hopefully get it into a good spot so we get some good reports going and you know, streamline some things and feel good about it.","index":972,"end_time":3349.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3342.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And at the end of the day.","index":973,"end_time":3350.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3350.01,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"It''S a really good opportunity to just.","index":974,"end_time":3352.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3350.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Peel back a bunch of layers that have been built and come up with.","index":975,"end_time":3355.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3352.05,"speaker_name":"Justin"},{"text":"A whole new foundation.","index":976,"end_time":3356.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3355.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":977,"end_time":3357.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3357.13,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Yeah, we would love that.","index":978,"end_time":3359.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3357.77,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"And then one more thing.","index":979,"end_time":3361.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3359.93,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"If you have to choose between leads and contacts, if you want my bias, I like contact records a lot better.","index":980,"end_time":3367.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3361.17,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"I think it''s easier for sales reps to just look at one object type instead of two and having two reports and putting that on maps and stuff.","index":981,"end_time":3376.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3367.89,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"So if you''re up in the air, I''ll push you over.","index":982,"end_time":3379.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3376.49,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"I lean that way too.","index":983,"end_time":3381.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3380.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And actually, Maria, HubSpot didn''t even have a lead object till like mid last year.","index":984,"end_time":3387.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3381.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Oh, wow.","index":985,"end_time":3388.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3387.61,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Okay.","index":986,"end_time":3388.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3388.21,"speaker_name":"Kyle Scoville"},{"text":"Yeah, so it was only contacts, but they did implement it on the sales side because.","index":987,"end_time":3392.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3388.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because there''s still a lot of HubSpot to Salesforce, you know, integrations.","index":988,"end_time":3397.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3392.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But a lot of our customers don''t even use that lead object at all.","index":989,"end_time":3402.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3398.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because it does get quite confusing, you.","index":990,"end_time":3405.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3402.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Know, and there''s, there''s less rules too.","index":991,"end_time":3406.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3405.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So you get a lot of not.","index":992,"end_time":3409.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3406.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Junk, but there''s a lot of like, you know, not clear.","index":993,"end_time":3413.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3409.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, messy data on the lead side because there''s not as many requirements and stuff like that.","index":994,"end_time":3419.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3413.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So sometimes it''s better just to get enough information for the contact, get that association with an account, you know, that, that helps keep the data clean downstream.","index":995,"end_time":3427.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3419.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because even when I was clicking through.","index":996,"end_time":3429.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3427.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, there''s a lot of duplicates.","index":997,"end_time":3430.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3429.28,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, Salesforce lets you know that all the time.","index":998,"end_time":3433.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3430.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Hey, you might have three records that are very similar, and that is the case.","index":999,"end_time":3436.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3433.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So, yeah, hopefully we can get through some of that.","index":1000,"end_time":3439.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3437.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But thank you so much.","index":1001,"end_time":3442.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3440.12,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Yeah, thank you both.","index":1002,"end_time":3443.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3442.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Appreciate you staying on.","index":1003,"end_time":3444.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3443.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Have a good weekend.","index":1004,"end_time":3445.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3444.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And.","index":1005,"end_time":3445.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3445.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And Barb will chat with you here soon.","index":1006,"end_time":3448.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3446.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Got it.","index":1007,"end_time":3449.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3448.69,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":1008,"end_time":3449.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3449.29,"speaker_name":"Maria"},{"text":"All right, thanks, everyone.","index":1009,"end_time":3450.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3449.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Thanks for you take care.","index":1010,"end_time":3453.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3451.33,"speaker_name":"Maria"}],"dateString":"2025-11-07T19:00:00.000Z","host_email":"tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89699979849?pwd=gCwoAEcIgnve6d5ofbkJaMVX2NsPYI.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,barb.willans@aquaticinformatics.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","barb.willans@aquaticinformatics.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01K8Y5Z3H8VP7G6DH216RN9PQR","organizer_email":"tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.83,"bullets":["Confirmed lead scoring model structure and differences between TL and PS webinar scores","Tristan aligned on field mappings and sync cadence across Salesforce and Marketo","Maria explained that lead stage is unused due to switch to task-based model","Team agreed Salesforce would be primary source of truth for HubSpot migration","Barb raised concerns about MQL data quality; current reports capture non-MQLs"],"highlights":[{"quote":"Lead score is engagement score plus demographic score.","speaker":"Justin"},{"quote":"We are calculating not just an MQL but what happens prior... What is a lead.","speaker":"Barb"},{"quote":"You can just ignore everything that''s going on here and build what is best practice.","speaker":"Maria"}],"topics":["lead scoring","integration","reporting","migration","data quality"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-11-11T21:06:59Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Salesforce-Marketo Integration and Lead Scoring**\n\nThe meeting clarified key aspects of the Salesforce-Marketo integration and lead scoring systems to ensure accurate data flow and lead qualification.\n\n- **The Salesforce-Marketo sync runs every five minutes**, moving new and updated data bidirectionally between the systems, as confirmed by Justin (04:23).  \n    - The integration uses the Marketo user for authentication, driving all sync activity.  \n    - Lead and contact objects sync is configured through field mapping within Marketo’s database management, distinguishing standard and custom fields.  \n    - Justin highlighted that certain custom objects sync differently and the default lead/contact sync settings remain mostly unchanged over time.  \n    - This frequent sync supports near real-time lead updates and accurate sales follow-up readiness.\n\n- **Lead scoring is driven by smart campaigns focused primarily on webinars and other activities** (05:36).  \n    - Product Showcase webinars assign **100 points** immediately, flagging attendees for follow-up, while Thought Leadership webinars score lower to reflect top-of-funnel engagement.  \n    - Scoring templates are managed centrally and copied for each webinar program, enabling consistent scoring practices.  \n    - The scoring model combines **engagement score** (actions like email clicks, webinar attendance) and **demographic score** (profile fit), which together create the total **lead score** that determines qualification.  \n    - Justin noted some legacy scoring fields exist but the person score in Marketo maps to the lead score in Salesforce, which currently drives lead qualification.\n\n## **Lead Lifecycle and Qualification Process**\n\nThe team reviewed the lead-to-contact conversion process and how Marketing Qualified Leads (MQLs) are created, managed, and reported.\n\n- **New leads created in Marketo flow into Salesforce as lead records and require manual conversion to contacts by BDRs** (08:44).  \n    - When a lead hits the **100-point MQL threshold**, a task is created for the BDR to qualify and convert the lead to a contact and account, creating an opportunity in the process.  \n    - Existing contacts generate new opportunities without conversion steps.  \n    - The BDR’s workflow centers on a task-based model rather than direct lead record updates, with qualification notes and statuses tracked in tasks (36:30).  \n    - Maria emphasized that lead and contact stages are not actively used in current processes, focusing instead on task completion and opportunity progression (14:25).\n\n- **MQL reporting is primarily based on task activity reports, capturing lead qualification events** (15:17).  \n    - Justin demonstrated a report filtering activities with subjects containing “Marketing Qualified Lead” since mid-September, showing qualification types like hand raise, bubble up, or trade show (18:35).  \n    - Barb noted discrepancies between reported MQL counts and actual qualified leads, highlighting that some reported leads are already opportunities or support requests, which inflates the numbers (51:15).  \n    - This gap underscores the need to refine MQL definitions and reporting logic to improve accuracy and alignment with sales (51:24).\n\n## **Data Source of Truth and Migration Considerations**\n\nThe discussion outlined strategic decisions about data sources and synchronization rules for upcoming HubSpot migration.\n\n- **Salesforce is preferred as the primary source of truth for contact and lead data**, supported unanimously by Maria, Justin, and Barb (26:38).  \n    - Salesforce contains comprehensive records, including those absent from Marketo due to scoring or activity thresholds.  \n    - Marketo holds some records not in Salesforce, but these tend to lack critical data such as email or company info, limiting their sales value (26:41).  \n    - Effective deduplication and bidirectional sync between Salesforce and HubSpot are critical to maintain data integrity during migration.  \n    - Maria stressed syncing deletions from Salesforce to HubSpot to avoid stale or dead contacts lingering in sales systems, while deletions in HubSpot should not remove contacts from Salesforce to preserve records (30:34).\n\n- **Business rules around contact deletion focus on removing bad or invalid data rather than non-responsive leads** (29:11).  \n    - Maria and Kyle cautioned against deleting contacts solely due to lack of engagement to avoid losing sales relationships.  \n    - The team discussed using automation and enrichment tools to clean dormant contacts quarterly or annually, minimizing manual cleanup burden (32:13).\n\n## **Lead Qualification Workflow and Reporting**\n\nThe meeting detailed the BDR qualification workflow and reporting fields critical to sales and marketing alignment.\n\n- **BDRs work primarily through Salesforce tasks linked to leads, updating contact attempts and qualification notes without changing lead stages directly** (35:53).  \n    - Blake, the sole BDR currently, tracks up to three contact attempts and adds free-form qualification notes that feed into opportunity records (36:30).  \n    - The qualification notes field drives multiple reports and includes keywords like “Direct Flip” to flag known opportunities needing no further qualification (42:50).  \n    - Maria and Kyle highlighted that automating “Direct Flip” handling would save BDR time and reduce manual effort (43:38).\n\n- **Opportunity stages and field history tracking support handoffs from BDRs to sales reps**, distinguishing between marketing-qualified prospects and sales-qualified leads (44:32).  \n    - Opportunities typically enter as “Generate Prospect” and move to “Qualified” once sales confirms interest, forming the basis for sales pipeline reporting.  \n    - The team acknowledged that “Generate Prospect” represents a limbo stage where marketing has qualified but sales has not yet accepted the lead (46:12).  \n    - Reports rely heavily on tracking these stage changes and qualification notes to measure pipeline health and BDR effectiveness.\n\n- **Current reporting relies on filtering task subjects and free-text qualification notes**, a process the team wants to replace with more structured fields in HubSpot for better accuracy and easier management (53:11).  \n    - Maria emphasized recreating the task-based concept in HubSpot but without custom tasks, aiming for cleaner data and improved reporting workflows (53:37).\n\n## **Product and System Strategy for HubSpot Migration**\n\nThe conversation concluded with strategic considerations for lead/contact management in HubSpot and system simplification.\n\n- **Preference exists for using contact records over leads in HubSpot to simplify sales workflows and reporting** (55:57).  \n    - Maria prefers contacts only, citing easier sales rep adoption and fewer duplicate or messy lead records.  \n    - Tristan noted HubSpot introduced a lead object only recently, with many customers choosing to avoid leads entirely to reduce complexity (56:20).  \n    - The HubSpot model can link contacts directly to accounts, reducing the need for manual lead conversion steps seen in Salesforce-Marketo flows (55:50).\n\n- **The migration offers an opportunity to redesign the foundation of lead and contact management**, shedding legacy complexity and building streamlined processes (55:50).  \n    - Justin and Tristan see this as a chance to peel back layers and enable a cleaner, more effective CRM and marketing automation setup.  \n    - This includes defining clear business rules, data flows, and success metrics aligned with both sales and marketing needs.  \n    - The team aims to improve reporting accuracy, reduce manual work for BDRs, and ensure data cleanliness post-migration.\n\n- **Ongoing collaboration between marketing, sales, and technical teams is critical** to finalize data definitions, reporting standards, and workflows before migration (53:11).  \n    - Barb, Maria, and Kyle will help clarify MQL definitions and reporting needs to guide system design.  \n    - Tristan and Kyle will leverage experience from similar HubSpot migrations to anticipate challenges and solutions.  \n    - The plan involves phased implementation with test contacts and iterative validation to ensure smooth transition.","outline":null,"keywords":["Marketo Salesforce integration","Lead scoring model","Marketing qualified leads (MQL)","Salesforce task management","Data migration HubSpot","Lead/contact lifecycle"],"overview":"- **Salesforce-Marketo Sync:** Runs every five minutes, ensuring real-time data flow and accurate lead updates.  \n- **Lead Scoring Method:** Webinars score leads using engagement and demographic metrics; 100 points for Product Showcase.  \n- **MQL Creation Process:** Leads become contacts when reaching 100 points; BDRs are tasked with conversion and opportunity creation.  \n- **Source of Truth:** Salesforce is preferred for accurate lead data; critical to manage deduplication during HubSpot migration.  \n- **Contact Strategy for HubSpot:** Focus on contacts over leads to simplify workflows; eliminates manual conversions and enhances reporting.  \n- **Collaborative Work:** Marketing and sales must agree on definitions and reporting to prepare for a successful migration process.","action_items":"\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nReview and document detailed lead scoring model tokens and workflow in Marketo for complete understanding (07:46)\nAnalyze Salesforce reporting on MQLs and opportunity creation to confirm data attributes for management reporting (15:17)\nAssess and plan testing strategy with creation of test contacts in Salesforce to understand data flow and field behavior without impacting live data (24:07)\nMap out lead and contact object use in HubSpot for migration, considering simplifying data model as per meeting discussion (55:00)\n\n**Maria**\nProvide further clarification on MQL definitions and usage within AQI marketing and sales processes (17:00)\nAssist with examples and review of Salesforce reporting and workflows, including qualification notes and task management (37:00)\nSupport decision making on synchronization rules between HubSpot and Salesforce for record deletion and data cleanliness (28:06)\n\n**Kyle Scoville**\nProvide links to test account and key Salesforce reports used by BDRs for replication/testing purposes (24:39)\nSupport review of daily/weekly marketing management dashboards and reports relevant to MQLs and sales qualification (47:26)\n\n**Barb Willans**\nShare key marketing daily management reports and clarify weekly vs daily meeting cadence (47:27)\nProvide insights on MQL reporting differences and challenges for improved accuracy moving forward (48:45)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"65733a79-dc2f-4d43-abe3-da34a12b71df","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
    '2025-11-11 20:38:02.129513+00',
