INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Baylee Gunnell and Kate Hahn',
  '## **SEO Content Refresh Strategy**

The team agreed to prioritize updating around **100 articles** to improve SEO performance and keep content aligned with evolving search behaviors (05:09).

- **Kushagra identified about 100 articles needing refresh or optimization based on outdated keywords and content structure** (05:19)  
    - These articles were initially created under older SEO strategies and now require updates to target current primary and secondary keywords.  
    - The refresh includes revising titles, meta descriptions, and internal content structure to better match search intent.  
    - Kushagra emphasized that recent changes in search behavior, especially with large language models (LLMs) affecting click rates, require content that aligns with AI-generated summaries Google favors.  
    - This approach aims to recover lost clicks and maintain strong impressions from high-value topics.

- **Priority labeling of articles into P0, P1, and P2 categories is already set based on business impact and goals** (11:07)  
    - This prioritization helps focus efforts on the most important content first, ensuring resource efficiency.  
    - Baylee will review this prioritization and respond with how many articles can be refreshed within current credit limits and timelines.  
    - Kate and Kaydee expect updates to proceed rapidly enough to consume credits faster than they accumulate, reflecting urgency to reduce backlog.  
    - The team sees this as a one-time large refresh project to address accumulated content gaps before year-end.

## **Content and SEO Technical Details**

The content refresh will not only update words but also focus on technical SEO elements and visual assets for improved engagement (11:34).

- **Internal linking structure will be maintained but reviewed for relevance, with recommendations for anchor text updates** (13:33)  
    - Kushagra confirmed existing internal links will mostly remain but welcomes suggestions to improve link text for clarity and SEO.  
    - Baylee suggested creating a mapping file showing current and recommended internal links to guide copy updates and maintain strategic link flow.  
    - Kaydee highlighted that understanding internal link targets helps align SEO and content strategies cohesively.  
    - This ensures search engines correctly understand site structure and content relationships.

- **Images in articles will be refreshed selectively, prioritizing visuals from authoritative user-generated content sources like Quora and Reddit** (12:34)  
    - Kushagra advised sourcing images primarily from these platforms to leverage their high trust and authority.  
    - The existing images will mostly be kept unless better alternatives are suggested and fit brand guidelines.  
    - The team is open to recommendations on adding more images to balance the currently text-heavy articles.  
    - This visual update aims to enhance user engagement and signal content freshness to search engines.

## **Project Management and Workflow**

Clear expectations around deliverables, formats, and timelines were established to ensure smooth execution of the content refresh (15:34).

- **The team requested a pace and volume estimate for how many articles can be refreshed within the current points budget** (15:44)  
    - Kate asked for a plan showing throughput so they can monitor credit usage and adjust priorities if needed.  
    - Baylee committed to providing this estimate via Slack within the next day, aligning capacity with business needs.  
    - The goal is to use points faster than they accumulate to reduce backlog efficiently before year-end deadlines.  
    - This transparency helps manage expectations and resource allocation realistically.

- **Deliverables will be shared as Word documents, but the team is open to using any templates recommended by the service provider** (17:02)  
    - Kaydee expressed interest in working with a template that supports clarity and easy editing.  
    - Kushagra agreed to this approach, which will help keep content updates consistent and streamlined.  
    - This format choice supports easy review and collaboration across marketing and SEO teams.  
    - It also facilitates faster turnaround on revisions and approvals.

## **Strategic Business Context and Goals**

The content refresh is part of a broader marketing reset aimed at closing out the year strong and improving competitive SEO positioning against emerging market challenges (02:52).

- **Kate highlighted this project as a key step in the broader marketing reset and end-of-year planning** (17:30)  
    - The refresh will help reduce the bank of unused credits and align content with updated business priorities.  
    - This effort supports the global digital marketing program led by Kaydee and the SEO strategy managed by Kushagra.  
    - Improving SEO rankings is critical to counter competition from large language models changing search dynamics.  
    - The project fits into a longer-term vision of keeping Bazaar Voice’s content authoritative and relevant amid evolving digital trends.

- **Baylee explained that Marketers In Demand, the parent company, is focused on growth through acquiring expertise like this SEO initiative** (04:25)  
    - This collaboration reflects a strategy to leverage outside partners to accelerate marketing impact quickly.  
    - Igor, the content strategist, brings SEO and content expertise critical for executing the refresh with precision.  
    - The partnership aims to deliver measurable improvements in keyword rankings, traffic, and user engagement.  
    - This approach also allows internal teams to focus on broader strategic goals beyond tactical content updates.

## **Content Quality and Validation**

The team agreed on the need to validate data points and possibly incorporate subject matter expert input where data is complex or critical (10:10).

- **Most content updates will target keyword optimization, but about 7-8 articles require detailed data validation or expert input** (10:10)  
    - Kushagra noted these articles rely on third-party data or proprietary information that must be checked carefully.  
    - Links to original data sources will be shared to help the content team verify facts and maintain accuracy.  
    - This ensures the refreshed content remains credible and authoritative in the eyes of users and search engines.  
    - It also reduces risk of outdated or incorrect information harming brand trust.

- **Baylee confirmed that the spreadsheet with article details will be shared promptly to enable smooth collaboration** (18:22)  
    - This document includes keywords, priority levels, and structural guidance to keep everyone aligned.  
    - Having this centralized resource will speed up content creation and review cycles.  
    - It also supports transparent progress tracking and issue resolution.  
    - The team agreed this coordination will be key to meeting tight deadlines effectively.',
  '2025-11-10 14:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Review the spreadsheet with article priorities and provide feedback on how many articles can be refreshed and at what pace (15:34)","completed":false},{"text":"Send a template for content deliverables for the Bazaar Voice team to adopt or adapt (16:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up via Slack later same day or next day with workload capacity and project timeline (16:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Bazaar Voice team to receive the spreadsheet of articles needing refresh and internal linking plans (18:22)","completed":false},{"text":"Mark articles in the spreadsheet with priority levels (P0, P1, P2) based on business strategy to guide refresh order (11:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Maintain existing internal links on the website while cooperating on suggested anchor text adjustments (13:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Attach and share third-party data source links used in articles for team validation and accuracy checks (10:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide spreadsheet containing keywords, article structure notes, and current SEO data for use by Marketers In Demand team (07:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Share spreadsheet and internal prioritization plans with Marketers In Demand (18:22)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide input on deliverable format preferences and usability of templates shared (16:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with marketing leadership and offsite activities but stay updated on the content refresh project (17:30)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
