-- Meeting: Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting (2025-11-07 17:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'bf57e936-b322-4b36-bf32-174d44c65e09',
    '2025-11-07 17:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01K9ADQAS9HMSYHZ0AM173J6KE',
    'Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Tim","Baylee Gunnell","Gab","Christina Bila"}'::text[],
    1682,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84384090979?pwd=CWYLaJlFxbjtxp2qyx0nk6skchlVVg.1',
    '{"id":"01K9ADQAS9HMSYHZ0AM173J6KE","title":"Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast and Content Launch**\n\nThe team is finalizing key podcast episodes and preparing to launch the ebook next Thursday, with a phased rollout strategy for related content.\n\n- **Ebook launch set for next Thursday** with foundational materials ready, while some minor edits will continue post-launch (01:15)  \n    - Gab plans to start assembling launch emails and internal communications on Monday.  \n    - Dawn is designing the landing page, expected by end of day today, supporting a smooth launch start.  \n    - Tim emphasized it''s acceptable if not all assets are perfect at launch since content will drip out over time.  \n    - The staged rollout approach reduces risk and allows iterative improvements.  \n\n- **Podcast production is on track with the episode featuring Michelle to be delivered by end of day** (02:23)  \n    - Upcoming guests include Callie Chapman from Prudential and Christine Froelich, with two to three more episodes scheduled for December.  \n    - Gab has submitted final feedback on LinkedIn carousel assets, allowing the MID team to schedule posts efficiently.  \n    - Tim recommended leading with guest focus rather than logos in promotional materials to maintain personal connection.  \n\n- **Decision to skip voiceover for compilation reels and rely on guest audio to preserve authenticity and save time** (09:07)  \n    - Tim expressed discomfort recording voiceovers, preferring guest voices to maintain natural podcast tone.  \n    - Team will proceed with edited clips without additional voiceover, speeding up content readiness.  \n\n## **Ebook Production and Guest Engagement**\n\nThe ebook design revisions are nearly complete, with final checks underway to enable timely guest communications and promotional efforts.\n\n- **Ebook visuals updated to replace problematic logos with thematic icons, addressing prior concerns about brand usage** (07:20)  \n    - Tim’s feedback on image sizing and slide transitions has been incorporated to enhance flow and visual clarity.  \n    - Baylee confirmed that the most recent revisions will be finalized today to allow guest outreach on Monday.  \n    - Tim will send personalized emails to guests Monday morning to acknowledge their contribution professionally without requesting approval.  \n    - Gab will follow up with launch day emails including promotional assets and partner marketing guides to amplify guest involvement.  \n\n- **Guest promo assets and social packages are prepared for internal and external sharing to maximize launch visibility** (13:06)  \n    - Employee advocacy systems have been updated to facilitate sharing across the organization, boosting organic reach.  \n    - Positive feedback on GIF assets from Ryan highlights strong internal reception and supports future creative investments.  \n\n## **Platform Access and Distribution Enhancements**\n\nEfforts to expand podcast reach focus on resolving access issues and enabling video content on Spotify to increase engagement.\n\n- **Persistent Apple login support challenges remain unresolved after five attempts, delaying access improvements** (04:51)  \n    - Spotify lacks a dedicated login, but a new shared account will be created to allow video uploads and asset access.  \n    - Baylee confirmed that uploading video to Spotify is a simple addition needing 2-5 extra minutes per episode.  \n    - Gab approved starting video uploads now rather than waiting until 2026, adding value without disrupting current workflows.  \n\n- **Separately uploading video content on Spotify requires distinct logins, which the team will set up and share for seamless collaboration** (06:11)  \n    - This move supports expanding media formats and aligns with broader content distribution goals.  \n\n## **Paid Marketing Campaign for Financial Lending Sector**\n\nA new paid campaign is underway to position the company early ahead of regulatory changes impacting mortgage qualification, with clear ownership and timelines.\n\n- **Campaign targets financial lenders and mortgage professionals in response to HR 2808, focusing on credit trigger sales impacts** (18:38)  \n    - Gab submitted detailed briefs to Baylee and the MID team for paid visuals and LinkedIn campaign setup.  \n    - Christina Bila will lead copy and visual strategy coordination, working closely with the MID team for campaign execution and optimization.  \n    - Anticipated progress update scheduled for next Friday to review creative assets and initial campaign results.  \n\n- **Christina to focus on paid strategy planning for 2026 with MID, leveraging Ideometry’s growth marketing expertise** (25:44)  \n    - The team agreed to hold a kickoff session to align on annual goals and integrate paid tactics into the broader marketing plan.  \n    - Baylee offered to provide comprehensive documentation and strategic guidance for long-term paid media efforts.  \n\n## **Vendor Relationship and Team Collaboration**\n\nThe team’s strong vendor partnership and internal coordination are recognized as key drivers of current success and future growth.\n\n- **Updated contract signed ahead of schedule, enabling continued collaboration through next year** (18:14)  \n    - Gab expressed surprise at the quick turnaround, underscoring the positive momentum.  \n    - Tim praised Baylee’s vendor management as exceptional, suggesting formal recognition or a raise to retain top talent.  \n    - The team’s ability to keep discussions focused and productive was highlighted as a major strength.  \n\n- **Marketers In Demand (MID) agency network capabilities explained to align expectations and promote cross-team collaboration** (22:25)  \n    - MID’s services include writing, video editing, animation, design, analytics, and advertising, supporting VARISC’s needs across multiple areas.  \n    - Team members shared insights on various agencies under MID, clarifying roles to reduce confusion and streamline future interactions.  \n    - The collaborative culture within MID encourages flexible support and innovation across projects, boosting overall marketing effectiveness.","outline":null,"keywords":["ebook launch","podcast episodes","LinkedIn carousel","Spotify video","paid social campaigns","marketing agency collaboration"],"overview":"- **Ebook Launch Date:** Ebook launching next Thursday; final edits ongoing, with some materials ready.  \n- **Podcast Progress:** Current episode due today; more guests lined up for December, with efficient promotional strategies.  \n- **Authentic Content Focus:** No voiceovers for reels; using only guest audio for a natural tone in podcasts.  \n- **Marketing Campaign Initiated:** New campaign targeting lenders responds to HR 2808; progress update expected next Friday.  \n- **Vendor Collaboration:** Updated contract signed early; strong management recognized as key to success and growth potential.  \n- **MID Network Introduction:** Clear roles and capabilities within the MID agency network to enhance collaboration across teams.","action_items":"\n**Gabrielle Verzella**\nFinalize and send launch day email to guests including partner marketing guide and assets, coordinating with Baylee to time outreach (13:30)\nCollaborate with Christina and MID team on paid campaign creative and copy, with initial review by next Friday (18:38)\nLead internal review and strategy discussion with Christina and Tim for 2026 growth marketing initiatives (25:44)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nFollow up post-meeting to confirm status and share near-final ebook PDF for guest outreach by Monday (12:08)\nCreate and share new Spotify login for video podcast uploads and coordinate with Gab and team for rollout (05:48)\nDrive finalization and scheduling of LinkedIn carousel posts and GIF promotional asset sharing (04:51)\nAssist Christina with onboarding to MID services, including an overview session and preparing growth marketing documentation (22:25)\nOrganize paid social kickoff session to shape annual strategy with Verisk team (26:54)\n\n**Tim Finnigan**\nProvide final notes and feedback on LinkedIn carousel visuals to MID (04:06)\nDecide on voiceover inclusion for compilation videos, opting to use guest audio only (09:07)\nComplete and send edited guest clips for professional courtesy outreach Monday (10:48)\nSubmit LinkedIn recommendation for Baylee recognizing outstanding vendor support (14:31)\nInform team when approved ebook PDF is available to distribute to guests (22:03)\n\n**Christina Bila**\nLead content creation and review for paid campaign targeting financial lending, coordinating with Gab and MID (18:38)\nEngage in strategic discussions with MID to align growth marketing efforts and explore agency services (22:25)\n"},"duration":28.040000915527344,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Tim"},{"id":1,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":2,"name":"Gab"},{"id":3,"name":"Christina Bila"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Bailey, can you hear me?","index":0,"end_time":4.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.76,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":1,"end_time":5.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":2,"end_time":7.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":6.64,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Hi.","index":3,"end_time":8.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":8.08,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Where are you located today, Tim?","index":4,"end_time":11.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"In my bunker in my basement.","index":5,"end_time":16.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.68,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":6,"end_time":17.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How are you all doing?","index":7,"end_time":24.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":23.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I love you.","index":8,"end_time":26.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.77,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Good.","index":9,"end_time":26.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":26.41,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s.","index":10,"end_time":27.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":26.77,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s Friday.","index":11,"end_time":28.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":27.29,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Thank goodness.","index":12,"end_time":30.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":29.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, chill.","index":13,"end_time":33.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.13,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"She''s coming.","index":14,"end_time":34.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":34.17,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Hi, Christina.","index":15,"end_time":36.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":35.93,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Hi, Bailey.","index":16,"end_time":40.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":39.29,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Don''t make fun of her.","index":17,"end_time":40.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.13,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Bailey, you and Christina haven''t met yet, right?","index":18,"end_time":43.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":41.53,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":19,"end_time":45.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":44.65,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"This is Christina.","index":20,"end_time":47.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Bailey.","index":21,"end_time":47.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":47.53,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Christina, Christina, Bailey.","index":22,"end_time":49.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":47.89,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Hey, Christina.","index":23,"end_time":50.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":49.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Super excited to be working together now.","index":24,"end_time":53.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes, me too.","index":25,"end_time":54.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":53.52,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I''ve heard a lot about you guys.","index":26,"end_time":55.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":54.44,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"We do some cool stuff.","index":27,"end_time":58.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":57.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ve been working on some cool projects.","index":28,"end_time":61.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s exciting.","index":29,"end_time":62.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":61.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we got lots going on.","index":30,"end_time":68.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re so close.","index":31,"end_time":70.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Next Thursday, right?","index":32,"end_time":72.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re.","index":33,"end_time":72.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":72.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re launching the ebook.","index":34,"end_time":74.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":72.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s the goal.","index":35,"end_time":76.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":75.36,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":36,"end_time":76.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":76.24,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"How are you feeling about.","index":37,"end_time":78.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"About it all?","index":38,"end_time":80,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s coming together.","index":39,"end_time":81.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":80.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Monday is probably going to be my day where I, like, start putting those launch pieces together of like.","index":40,"end_time":89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":83.68,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"All right, email 1.","index":41,"end_time":90.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":89,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Internal comms, having the actual PDF of the ebook on the website.","index":42,"end_time":95.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":90.72,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Like, it''s coming along.","index":43,"end_time":97.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":95.68,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Dawn is designing her landing page.","index":44,"end_time":100.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":97.68,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Hopefully we''ll see something by end of day today.","index":45,"end_time":103.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.24,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But I think it''s coming together and it''s okay if we don''t have absolutely everything ready to go at launch because it''s going to drip out over time.","index":46,"end_time":115.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":104.64,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So as long as we have those, like, fundamental pieces for getting it out there at first, that''s great.","index":47,"end_time":123.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":115.92,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Good perspective.","index":48,"end_time":125.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":124,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We do have a. I feel like a lot of stuff should be ready by the launch, but there might be a few straggling things that we finish just.","index":49,"end_time":133.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":125.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just edits on.","index":50,"end_time":134.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":133.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":51,"end_time":135.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":135.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like the comp reals was something I was thinking about, and I''m sure we''ll talk through that as we go through.","index":52,"end_time":142.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":135.84,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"If you have slides today.","index":53,"end_time":143.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":142.04,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":54,"end_time":143.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":143.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, yeah, yeah, we''ll just get into those slides.","index":55,"end_time":148.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":144.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So then just starting on podcast updates.","index":56,"end_time":156.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":154.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then we''ll get to the ebook, and then we have the PID GIF promotion, and then we''ll take a look at Pulse.","index":57,"end_time":164.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":156.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":58,"end_time":165.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":164.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So just starting with the podcast, I feel like this episode is a little old at this point, but just the most recent one.","index":59,"end_time":177.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we''re wrapping up the episode with Michelle.","index":60,"end_time":180.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":177.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We should be able to send that over to you by the end of today.","index":61,"end_time":182.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":180.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then everything should be updated to have the Instagram graphics moving forward.","index":62,"end_time":190.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So excited for that.","index":63,"end_time":192.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":190.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, looking forward to that.","index":64,"end_time":193.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":192.55,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Hey, Bailey.","index":65,"end_time":197.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":195.35,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"And then what''s coming is I''ve got woman named Kelly Kaylee.","index":66,"end_time":203.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.23,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":67,"end_time":204.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.23,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"I''m getting Bailey and Callie Chapman from Prudential.","index":68,"end_time":209.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.71,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"She''s next week.","index":69,"end_time":210.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.11,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"And then I have an internal One with Christine Froelich and maybe have another one.","index":70,"end_time":215.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210.31,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"But we''re going to try to spread those out away from the launch, so they''re probably more December ish, but we''ll probably have two or three more podcasts coming.","index":71,"end_time":226.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":215.82,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":72,"end_time":227.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Good.","index":73,"end_time":229.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Exciting.","index":74,"end_time":229.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":229.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I think we were just waiting for your final notes on the episode on those LinkedIn carousels for the episode with Stephen.","index":75,"end_time":238.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I put my feedback in.","index":76,"end_time":240.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":239.22,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But Tim, you had mentioned wanting to talk about those.","index":77,"end_time":243.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":240.7,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I just want to be careful about using the logos.","index":78,"end_time":252.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.18,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"I''d rather lead with the person than the logo.","index":79,"end_time":257.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.38,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"There was just one character.","index":80,"end_time":261.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.62,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"I think you''re thinking of the TMR ebook GIF package is probably what you''re looking at.","index":81,"end_time":269.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":262.66,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Oh, and then the other one.","index":82,"end_time":271.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":270.51,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"And then the other thing.","index":83,"end_time":273.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.19,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"The only other comment I had was more of the ebook too, with the smaller picture.","index":84,"end_time":276.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.03,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"But Don and Gab captured my thoughts as well, so I had nothing on Steven.","index":85,"end_time":282.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.79,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":86,"end_time":284.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":282.75,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So then my feedback is final and then the MID team can update those and I can.","index":87,"end_time":289.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":284.11,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I can schedule them out.","index":88,"end_time":291.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":289.87,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":89,"end_time":292.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":291.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll just get those all wrapped up then.","index":90,"end_time":294.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then Gab.","index":91,"end_time":297.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"A couple weeks ago we had talked about the challenges of getting Apple login.","index":92,"end_time":305.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":297.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I spent a lot of time trying to get a hold of their support team.","index":93,"end_time":310.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":307.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They have not gotten back to me.","index":94,"end_time":312.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ve reached out about five times and still have not heard anything about the original login.","index":95,"end_time":319.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":312.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I did figure out with Spotify, though, there wasn''t a separate login created for that.","index":96,"end_time":325.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":321,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we could create something new for that that we all just have access to.","index":97,"end_time":331.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we can get a deeper dive of the Spotify assets.","index":98,"end_time":335.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":331.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we had also, I mean, this came up because we can do video on Spotify now.","index":99,"end_time":340.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.479,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So if you want to do that, we can start posting video on Spotify if you want.","index":100,"end_time":345.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And just create a separate login there.","index":101,"end_time":347.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":345.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, is it something that you think is okay to start now or do we Start fresh in 26?","index":102,"end_time":356.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":348.51,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It doesn''t hurt to start now.","index":103,"end_time":360.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":104,"end_time":361.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, we already have the video for everything.","index":105,"end_time":363.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, it.","index":106,"end_time":365.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":364.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''ll just take an extra two to five minutes per episode to get the video uploaded.","index":107,"end_time":370.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":365.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":108,"end_time":371.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":370.91,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":109,"end_time":372.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s.","index":110,"end_time":372.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":372.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s really easy.","index":111,"end_time":373.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":372.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We.","index":112,"end_time":373.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can get the account set up for you if you want us to, and we''ll just share the login information so we can all get in there.","index":113,"end_time":381.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then sometimes I like to go back like the last five episodes and get it uploaded.","index":114,"end_time":387.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":381.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then it''s super easy to add the Video.","index":115,"end_time":389.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":387.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":116,"end_time":390.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":117,"end_time":391.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":390.64,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So it''s separate from Buzzsprout.","index":118,"end_time":392.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":391.04,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":119,"end_time":393.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You do have to upload it separately.","index":120,"end_time":394.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":121,"end_time":395.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":122,"end_time":396.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":123,"end_time":396.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":396.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I support y'' all going ahead and creating that login.","index":124,"end_time":401.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":397.44,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And that''s just one.","index":125,"end_time":403.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":401.88,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"One small thing I can add to our process.","index":126,"end_time":405.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":403.2,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s fine.","index":127,"end_time":406.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":128,"end_time":407.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":406.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We will work on that then.","index":129,"end_time":410.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":409.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":130,"end_time":411.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":411.14,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And now for the ebook.","index":131,"end_time":414.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":412.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''re just working on wrapping up those ebook design revisions.","index":132,"end_time":419.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":415.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The guest creatives, with your feedback.","index":133,"end_time":422.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think that was one of the notes you had, Tim, too, on just making the images smaller and.","index":134,"end_time":428.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And all that good stuff.","index":135,"end_time":430.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":428.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I think this might have also been part of what you were talking about, Tim, with the logos is for these.","index":136,"end_time":439.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, and so Don and I were talking last week, Tim, and we said the solve for that is just replace it with the kind of, like, little icons of the robot, the.","index":137,"end_time":453.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.75,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Whatever those three are, because it trickles into those three pillars anyway, so.","index":138,"end_time":457.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.63,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So that troubleshoots the logo issue.","index":139,"end_time":461.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":458.21,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay.","index":140,"end_time":462.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":462.21,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Okay.","index":141,"end_time":463.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":463.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So did you have any other edits on these.","index":142,"end_time":466.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":463.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I may have dropped?","index":143,"end_time":471.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":469.97,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I think I see, like, one comment on the first.","index":144,"end_time":475.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.85,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":145,"end_time":476.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":475.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Concept.","index":146,"end_time":477.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And really, that note was just me saying, like, this looks great.","index":147,"end_time":480.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.17,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I just want to make sure that, like, the time.","index":148,"end_time":482.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":480.65,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"The gap of time between the second slide and, like, the fourth slide feels more seamless.","index":149,"end_time":491.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.73,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But.","index":150,"end_time":491.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":491.47,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what I said.","index":151,"end_time":493.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":491.99,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":152,"end_time":494.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":493.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":153,"end_time":494.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":494.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I took a look at this yesterday, so I think we should be able to make that happen.","index":154,"end_time":499.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":494.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll keep an eye on it, though.","index":155,"end_time":501.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":500.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":156,"end_time":502.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":502.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And we''ll just get started on the animations here.","index":157,"end_time":505.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":502.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":158,"end_time":506.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":505.51,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":159,"end_time":506.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":506.31,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Otherwise, I had no feedback.","index":160,"end_time":507.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":506.59,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay.","index":161,"end_time":508.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":508.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I think we just barely sent over the updated LinkedIn carousel copy.","index":162,"end_time":514.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":509.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The case study was something mentioned in the episode, so I think we''re.","index":163,"end_time":519.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":515.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re good there.","index":164,"end_time":520.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then what do you want to do about the compilation videos?","index":165,"end_time":526.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":521.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know we talked about recording some stuff, but sounds like it''s been pretty crazy.","index":166,"end_time":533.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":528.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":167,"end_time":534.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":533.95,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Tim, do you want to record some voiceover for the comp Reals or do we want to move forward without that and just put.","index":168,"end_time":543.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":534.91,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Put it.","index":169,"end_time":543.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":543.55,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Piece it together with just the guest clips and some post?","index":170,"end_time":547.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":543.99,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Copy that.","index":171,"end_time":550.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":547.59,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"This has been, like, the bane of my existence because I.","index":172,"end_time":554.229,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.47,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"One day I''m like, oh, this is value.","index":173,"end_time":557.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":555.03,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"The other, I''m like, do I need to do this?","index":174,"end_time":559.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.43,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"And I''m traveling so much.","index":175,"end_time":563.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":560.63,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"I''m having trouble doing it without.","index":176,"end_time":565.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":563.23,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"And I want it to be in my voice, Bailey.","index":177,"end_time":568.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.69,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"So I. I''m at that point where either I do it, and I just trust that what you guys came up with is resonating or is it in my voice?","index":178,"end_time":581.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.01,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"So I don''t.","index":179,"end_time":583.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":581.65,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"I. I''m so wishy washy on this.","index":180,"end_time":586.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":583.69,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Like, is it going to move?","index":181,"end_time":588.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":586.73,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"The needle is really for the time that I put into it.","index":182,"end_time":591.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.13,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"I mean, we already have them edited without your voice over in between, so we just wanted to get prepped so we could plug them in super fast.","index":183,"end_time":602.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":593.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''ll get the team to put it together so you can see how they are right now.","index":184,"end_time":606.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":602.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That would be great because one of the things that''s nice about the actual podcast is the inflection of their voice and like it''s a conversation versus me recording it.","index":185,"end_time":622.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.05,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Because I''ve done the intros and outros of recording it and it sounds so like, I''ll relist to him.","index":186,"end_time":628.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":622.21,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Like, oh, this is so cringe that I''m like, I don''t.","index":187,"end_time":631.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":628.45,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"I.","index":188,"end_time":632.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":632.01,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"And that''s just me.","index":189,"end_time":633.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":632.37,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"So I think it might be better just to go with the guest and have it be their voice with the quote and go forward.","index":190,"end_time":642.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.689,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Okay, well, we''ll do that.","index":191,"end_time":645.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":643.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Speaking of the guest, I need to send the.","index":192,"end_time":651.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":648.02,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"At least the cleaned up version of what I edited last week.","index":193,"end_time":656.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":652.02,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"I want to be able to send that on Monday to all the guests.","index":194,"end_time":660.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.9,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Will we be able to get that?","index":195,"end_time":662.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":660.62,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Because I''m just gonna.","index":196,"end_time":663.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.5,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"It''s just gonna be a, like, hey, congratulations, you''re part of this thing.","index":197,"end_time":668.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":663.74,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"I really loved.","index":198,"end_time":670.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.51,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"The reason why I picked it is because you said this and it really fits in well with what I''m talking about.","index":199,"end_time":675.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.39,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"There''s going to be no ask of, hey, are you okay with it?","index":200,"end_time":680.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":675.99,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"It''s going to be just as a.","index":201,"end_time":683.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.63,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"What do you call it?","index":202,"end_time":685.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":684.63,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Not being polite, but as a professional courtesy.","index":203,"end_time":689.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.31,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Are you talking about like having the designed ebook?","index":204,"end_time":695.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":691.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yep.","index":205,"end_time":697.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":696.79,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Like, how.","index":206,"end_time":698.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.07,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Where are we with the edits?","index":207,"end_time":699.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.63,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"It doesn''t have to be the final final, but it, if it''s close, would be because I put.","index":208,"end_time":705.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.99,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"There was like 10 edits that I put in there with because there was some title titles that were wrong.","index":209,"end_time":711.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.43,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"There were some pictures that were.","index":210,"end_time":712.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":711.03,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"You guys got Ian Steves and Ian Dewar mixed up.","index":211,"end_time":716.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":712.71,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"So I just want to make sure that that''s.","index":212,"end_time":718.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":716.43,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Some of that stuff''s done where I can now send it to him and say, hey, there''s going to be a, you know, a couple tweaks to it, but I don''t want them to go edit it.","index":213,"end_time":727.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.39,"speaker_name":"Tim"},{"text":"Yes, let''s.","index":214,"end_time":729.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":728.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":